00080 void pyne::pyne_start() {
00081 #if defined __WIN_MSVC__
00082   char * tmpPYNE_DATA;
00083   size_t lenPYNE_DATA;
00084   errno_t errPYNE_DATA = _dupenv_s(&tmpPYNE_DATA, &lenPYNE_DATA, "PYNE_DATA");
00085   if (errPYNE_DATA)
00086     tmpPYNE_DATA = (char *) "<NOT_FOUND>";
00087   PYNE_DATA = (std::string) tmpPYNE_DATA;
00088 
00089   char * tmpNUC_DATA_PATH;
00090   size_t lenNUC_DATA_PATH;
00091   errno_t errNUC_DATA_PATH = _dupenv_s(&tmpNUC_DATA_PATH, &lenNUC_DATA_PATH, "NUC_DATA_PATH");
00092   if (errPYNE_DATA)
00093     tmpNUC_DATA_PATH = (char *) "<NOT_FOUND>";
00094   NUC_DATA_PATH = (std::string) tmpNUC_DATA_PATH;
00095 #else
00096   char * tmppath;
00097   tmppath = getenv("PYNE_DATA");
00098   if (tmppath == NULL)
00099       tmppath = (char *) "<NOT_FOUND>";
00100   PYNE_DATA = std::string(tmppath);
00101 
00102   tmppath = getenv("NUC_DATA_PATH");
00103   if (tmppath == NULL)
00104       tmppath = (char *) "<NOT_FOUND>";
00105   NUC_DATA_PATH = std::string(tmppath);
00106 #endif
00107   return;
00108 };

00146 double pyne::endftod_cpp(char * s) {
00147   // Converts string from ENDF only handles "E-less" format but is 5x faster
00148   int pos, mant, exp;
00149   double v, dbl_exp;
00150 
00151   mant = exp = 0;
00152   if (s[2] == '.') {
00153     // Convert an ENDF float
00154     if (s[9] == '+' or s[9] == '-') {
00155       // All these factors of ten are from place values.
00156       mant = s[8] + 10 * s[7] + 100 * s[6] + 1000 * s[5] + 10000 * s[4] + \
00157              100000 * s[3] + 1000000 * s[1] - 1111111 * '0';
00158       exp = s[10] - '0';
00159       // Make the right power of 10.
00160       dbl_exp = exp & 01? 10.: 1;
00161       dbl_exp *= (exp >>= 1) & 01? 100.: 1;
00162       dbl_exp *= (exp >>= 1) & 01? 1.0e4: 1;
00163       dbl_exp *= (exp >>= 1) & 01? 1.0e8: 1;
00164       // Adjust for powers of ten from treating mantissa as an integer.
00165       dbl_exp = (s[9] == '-'? 1/dbl_exp: dbl_exp) * 1.0e-6;
00166       // Get mantissa sign, apply exponent.
00167       v = mant * (s[0] == '-'? -1: 1) * dbl_exp;
00168     }
00169     else {
00170       mant = s[7] + 10 * s[6] + 100 * s[5] + 1000 * s[4] + 10000 * s[3] + \
00171              100000 * s[1] - 111111 * '0';
00172       exp = s[10] + 10 * s[9] - 11 * '0';
00173       dbl_exp = exp & 01? 10.: 1;
00174       dbl_exp *= (exp >>= 1) & 01? 100.: 1;
00175       dbl_exp *= (exp >>= 1) & 01? 1.0e4: 1;
00176       dbl_exp *= (exp >>= 1) & 01? 1.0e8: 1;
00177       dbl_exp *= (exp >>= 1) & 01? 1.0e16: 1;
00178       dbl_exp *= (exp >>= 1) & 01? 1.0e32: 1;
00179       dbl_exp *= (exp >>= 1) & 01? 1.0e64: 1;
00180       dbl_exp = (s[8] == '-'? 1/dbl_exp: dbl_exp) * 1.0e-5;
00181       v = mant * (s[0] == '-'? -1: 1) * dbl_exp;
00182     }
00183   }
00184 
00185   // Convert an ENDF int to float; we start from the last char in the field and
00186   // move forward until we hit a non-digit.
00187   else {
00188     v = 0;
00189     mant = 1; // Here we use mant for the place value about to be read in.
00190     pos = 10;
00191     while (s[pos] != '-' and s[pos] != '+' and s[pos] != ' ' and pos > 0) {
00192       v += mant * (s[pos] - '0');
00193       mant *= 10;
00194       pos--;
00195     }
00196     v *= (s[pos] == '-'? -1: 1);
00197   }
00198   return v;
00199 }

00201 double pyne::endftod_f(char * s) {
00202 #ifdef PYNE_IS_AMALGAMATED
00203   return endftod_cpp(s);
00204 #else
00205   return endftod_(s, 12);
00206 #endif
00207 }

00215 std::string pyne::to_upper(std::string s) {
00216   // change each element of the string to upper case.
00217   for(unsigned int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++)
00218     s[i] = toupper(s[i]);
00219   return s;
00220 }

00222 std::string pyne::to_lower(std::string s) {
00223   // change each element of the string to lower case
00224   for(unsigned int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++)
00225     s[i] = tolower(s[i]);
00226   return s;
00227 }

00229 
00230 std::string pyne::capitalize(std::string s) {
00231   unsigned int slen = s.length();
00232   if (slen == 0)
00233     return s;
00234   // uppercase the first character
00235   s[0] = toupper(s[0]);
00236   // change each subsequent element of the string to lower case
00237   for(unsigned int i = 1; i < slen; i++)
00238     s[i] = tolower(s[i]);
00239   return s;
00240 }

00243 std::string pyne::get_flag(char line[], int max_l) {
00244   char tempflag [10];
00245   for (int i = 0; i < max_l; i++)
00246   {
00247     if (line[i] == '\t' || line[i] == '\n' || line[i] == ' ' || line[i] == '\0')
00248     {
00249       tempflag[i] = '\0';
00250       break;
00251     }
00252     else
00253       tempflag[i] = line[i];
00254   }
00255   return std::string (tempflag);
00256 }

00260 std::string pyne::remove_substring(std::string s, std::string substr) {
00261   // Removes a substring from the string s
00262   int n_found = s.find(substr);
00263   while ( 0 <= n_found ) {
00264     s.erase( n_found , substr.length() );
00265     n_found = s.find(substr);
00266   }
00267   return s;
00268 }
00269 
00270 
00271 std::string pyne::remove_characters(std::string s, std::string chars) {
00272   // Removes all characters in the string chars from the string s
00273   for (int i = 0; i < chars.length(); i++ ) {
00274     s = remove_substring(s, chars.substr(i, 1) );
00275   }
00276   return s;
00277 }

00279 
00280 std::string pyne::replace_all_substrings(std::string s, std::string substr, std::string repstr) {
00281   // Replaces all instance of substr in s with the string repstr
00282   int n_found = s.find(substr);
00283   while ( 0 <= n_found ) {
00284     s.replace( n_found , substr.length(), repstr );
00285     n_found = s.find(substr);
00286   }
00287   return s;
00288 };

00305   // Returns true id a <= b <= c and flase otherwise.

00310 bool pyne::contains_substring(std::string s, std::string substr) {
00311   // Returns a boolean based on if the sub is in s.
00312   int n = s.find(substr);
00313   return ( 0 <= n && n < s.length() );
00314 }

00316 
00317 std::string pyne::natural_naming(std::string name) {
00318   // Calculates a version on the string name that is a valid
00319   // variable name, ie it uses only word characters.
00320   std::string nat_name (name);
00321 
00322   // Replace Whitespace characters with underscores
00323   nat_name = pyne::replace_all_substrings(nat_name, " ",  "_");
00324   nat_name = pyne::replace_all_substrings(nat_name, "\t", "_");
00325   nat_name = pyne::replace_all_substrings(nat_name, "\n", "_");
00326 
00327   // Remove non-word characters
00328   int n = 0;
00329   while ( n < nat_name.length() ) {
00330     if ( pyne::words.find(nat_name[n]) == std::string::npos )
00331       nat_name.erase(n, 1);
00332     else
00333       n++;
00334   }
00335 
00336   // Make sure that the name in non-empty before continuing
00337   if (nat_name.length() == 0)
00338     return nat_name;
00339 
00340   // Make sure that the name doesn't begin with a number.
00341   if ( pyne::digits.find(nat_name[0]) != std::string::npos)
00342     nat_name.insert(0, "_");
00343 
00344   return nat_name;
00345 };

00352 double pyne::slope(double x2, double y2, double x1, double y1) {
00353   // Finds the slope of a line.
00354   return (y2 - y1) / (x2 - x1);
00355 };
00356 
00357 
00358 double pyne::solve_line(double x, double x2, double y2, double x1, double y1) {
00359   return (slope(x2,y2,x1,y1) * (x - x2)) + y2;
00360 };

00373 // File Helpers
00374 
00375 bool pyne::file_exists(std::string strfilename) {
00376   // Thank you intarwebz for this function!
00377   // Sepcifically: http://www.techbytes.ca/techbyte103.html
00378   struct stat stFileInfo;
00379   bool blnReturn;
00380   int intStat;
00381 
00382   // Attempt to get the file attributes
00383   intStat = stat(strfilename.c_str(), &stFileInfo);
00384 
00385   if(intStat == 0) {
00386     // We were able to get the file attributes
00387     // so the file obviously exists.
00388     blnReturn = true;
00389   }
00390   else {
00391     // We were not able to get the file attributes.
00392     // This may mean that we don't have permission to
00393     // access the folder which contains this file. If you
00394     // need to do that level of checking, lookup the
00395     // return values of stat which will give you
00396     // more details on why stat failed.
00397     blnReturn = false;
00398   }
00399 
00400   return(blnReturn);
00401 };

02428 /*** Constructs zz to LL dictionary **/
02429 pyne::nucname::zzname_t pyne::nucname::get_zz_name()
02430 {
02431   zzname_t zld;
02432   for (name_zz_iter i = name_zz.begin(); i != name_zz.end(); i++)
02433   {
02434     zld[i->second] = i->first;
02435   }
02436   return zld;
02437 };

02608 /******************************************/
02609 /*** Define useful elemental group sets ***/
02610 /******************************************/
02611 
02612 pyne::nucname::zz_group pyne::nucname::name_to_zz_group(pyne::nucname::name_group eg)
02613 {
02614   zz_group zg;
02615   for (name_group_iter i = eg.begin(); i != eg.end(); i++)
02616     zg.insert(name_zz[*i]);
02617   return zg;
02618 };

02666 /***************************/
02667 /*** isnuclide functions ***/
02668 /***************************/
02669 
02670 bool pyne::nucname::isnuclide(std::string nuc) {
02671   int n;
02672   try {
02673     n = id(nuc);
02674   }
02675   catch(NotANuclide) {
02676     return false;
02677   }
02678   catch(IndeterminateNuclideForm) {
02679     return false;
02680   };
02681   return isnuclide(n);
02682 };
02683 
02684 bool pyne::nucname::isnuclide(const char * nuc) {
02685   return isnuclide(std::string(nuc));
02686 };
02687 
02688 bool pyne::nucname::isnuclide(int nuc) {
02689   int n;
02690   try {
02691     n = id(nuc);
02692   }
02693   catch(NotANuclide) {
02694     return false;
02695   }
02696   catch(IndeterminateNuclideForm) {
02697     return false;
02698   };
02699   if (n <= 10000000)
02700     return false;
02701   int zzz = n / 10000000;
02702   int aaa = (n % 10000000) / 10000;
02703   if (aaa == 0)
02704     return false;  // is element
02705   else if (aaa < zzz)
02706     return false;
02707   return true;
02708 };
02709 
02710 
02711 
02712 /********************/
02713 /*** id functions ***/
02714 /********************/
02715 int pyne::nucname::id(int nuc) {
02716   if (nuc < 0)
02717     throw NotANuclide(nuc, "");
02718 
02719   int newnuc;
02720   int zzz = nuc / 10000000;     // ZZZ ?
02721   int aaassss = nuc % 10000000; // AAA-SSSS ?
02722   int aaa = aaassss / 10000;    // AAA ?
02723   int ssss = aaassss % 10000;   // SSSS ?
02724   // Nuclide must already be in id form
02725   if (0 < zzz && zzz <= aaa && aaa <= zzz * 7) {
02726     // Normal nuclide
02727     if (5 < ssss){
02728     // Unphysical metastable state warning 
02729      warning("You have indicated a metastable state of " + pyne::to_str(ssss) + ". Metastable state above 5, possibly unphysical. ");
02730     }
02731     return nuc;
02732   } else if (aaassss == 0 && 0 < zz_name.count(zzz)) {
02733     // Natural elemental nuclide:  ie for Uranium = 920000000
02734     return nuc;
02735   } else if (nuc < 1000 && 0 < zz_name.count(nuc))
02736     //  Gave Z-number
02737     return nuc * 10000000;
02738 
02739   // Not in id form, try  ZZZAAAM form.
02740   zzz = nuc / 10000;     // ZZZ ?
02741   aaassss = nuc % 10000; // AAA-SSSS ?
02742   aaa = aaassss / 10;    // AAA ?
02743   ssss = nuc % 10;       // SSSS ?          
02744   if (zzz <= aaa && aaa <= zzz * 7) {
02745     // ZZZAAAM nuclide
02746     if (5 < ssss){
02747     // Unphysical metastable state warning
02748       warning("You have indicated a metastable state of " + pyne::to_str(ssss) + ". Metastable state above 5, possibly unphysical. ");
02749     }
02750     return (zzz*10000000) + (aaa*10000) + (nuc%10);
02751   } else if (aaa <= zzz && zzz <= aaa * 7 && 0 < zz_name.count(aaa)) {
02752     // Cinder-form (aaazzzm), ie 2350920
02753     if (5 < ssss){
02754     // Unphysical metastable state warning
02755       warning("You have indicated a metastable state of " + pyne::to_str(ssss) + ". Metastable state above 5, possibly unphysical. ");
02756     }
02757     return (aaa*10000000) + (zzz*10000) + (nuc%10);
02758   }
02759   //else if (aaassss == 0 && 0 == zz_name.count(nuc/1000) && 0 < zz_name.count(zzz))
02760   else if (aaassss == 0 && 0 < zz_name.count(zzz)) {
02761     // zzaaam form natural nuclide
02762     return zzz * 10000000;
02763   }
02764 
02765   if (nuc >= 1000000){
02766     // From now we assume no metastable info has been given.
02767     throw IndeterminateNuclideForm(nuc, "");
02768   };
02769 
02770   // Nuclide is not in zzaaam form, 
02771   // Try MCNP form, ie zzaaa
02772   // This is the same form as SZA for the 0th state.
02773   zzz = nuc / 1000;
02774   aaa = nuc % 1000; 
02775   if (zzz <= aaa) {
02776     if (aaa - 400 < 0) {
02777       if (nuc == 95242)
02778         return nuc * 10000 + 1;  // special case MCNP Am-242m
02779       else
02780         return nuc * 10000;  // Nuclide in normal MCNP form
02781     } else {
02782       // Nuclide in MCNP metastable form
02783       if (nuc == 95642)
02784         return (95642 - 400)*10000;  // special case MCNP Am-242
02785       nuc = ((nuc - 400) * 10000) + 1;
02786       while (3.0 < (float ((nuc/10000)%1000) / float (nuc/10000000)))
02787         nuc -= 999999;
02788       return nuc;
02789     }
02790   } else if (aaa == 0 && 0 < zz_name.count(zzz)) {
02791     // MCNP form natural nuclide
02792     return zzz * 10000000;
02793   }
02794 
02795   // Not a normal nuclide, might be a 
02796   // Natural elemental nuclide.  
02797   // ie 92 for Uranium = 920000
02798   if (0 < zz_name.count(nuc))
02799     return nuc * 10000000;
02800   throw IndeterminateNuclideForm(nuc, "");
02801 };
02802 
02803 int pyne::nucname::id(const char * nuc) {
02804   std::string newnuc (nuc);
02805   return id(newnuc);
02806 };
02807 
02808 int pyne::nucname::id(std::string nuc) {
02809   size_t npos = std::string::npos;
02810   if (nuc.empty())
02811     throw NotANuclide(nuc, "<empty>");
02812   int newnuc;
02813   std::string elem_name;
02814   int dash1 = nuc.find("-"); 
02815   int dash2;
02816   if (dash1 == npos)
02817     dash2 = npos;
02818   else
02819     dash2 = nuc.find("-", dash1+1);
02820   
02821   // nuc must be at least 4 characters or greater if it is in ZZLLAAAM form.
02822   if (nuc.length() >= 5 && dash1 != npos && dash2 != npos) {
02823     // Nuclide most likely in ZZLLAAAM Form, only form that contains two "-"'s.
02824     std::string zz = nuc.substr(0, dash1);
02825     std::string ll = nuc.substr(dash1+1, dash2);
02826     int zz_int = to_int(zz);
02827     // Verifying that the LL and ZZ point to the same element as secondary
02828     if(znum(ll) != zz_int)
02829       throw NotANuclide(nuc, "mismatched znum and chemical symbol");
02830     return zzllaaam_to_id(nuc);
02831   }
02832 
02833   // Get the string into a regular form
02834   std::string nucstr = pyne::to_upper(nuc);
02835   nucstr = pyne::remove_substring(nucstr, "-");
02836   int nuclen = nucstr.length();
02837 
02838   if (pyne::contains_substring(pyne::digits, nucstr.substr(0, 1))) {
02839     if (pyne::contains_substring(pyne::digits, nucstr.substr(nuclen-1, nuclen))) {
02840       // Nuclide must actually be an integer that 
02841       // just happens to be living in string form.
02842       newnuc = pyne::to_int(nucstr);
02843       newnuc = id(newnuc);
02844     } else {
02845       // probably in NIST-like form (242Am)
02846       // Here we know we have both digits and letters
02847       std::string anum_str = pyne::remove_characters(nucstr, pyne::alphabet);
02848       newnuc = pyne::to_int(anum_str) * 10000;
02849 
02850       // Add the Z-number
02851       elem_name = pyne::remove_characters(nucstr, pyne::digits);
02852       elem_name = pyne::capitalize(elem_name);
02853       if (0 < name_zz.count(elem_name))
02854         newnuc = (10000000 * name_zz[elem_name]) + newnuc;
02855       else
02856         throw NotANuclide(nucstr, newnuc);
02857     };
02858   } else if (pyne::contains_substring(pyne::alphabet, nucstr.substr(0, 1))) {
02859     // Nuclide is probably in name form, or some variation therein
02860     std::string anum_str = pyne::remove_characters(nucstr, pyne::alphabet);
02861 
02862     // natural element form, a la 'U' -> 920000000
02863     if (anum_str.empty()) {
02864       elem_name = pyne::capitalize(nucstr);    
02865       if (0 < name_zz.count(elem_name))
02866         return 10000000 * name_zz[elem_name]; 
02867     }
02868 
02869     int anum = pyne::to_int(anum_str);
02870 
02871     // bad form
02872     if (anum < 0)
02873       throw NotANuclide(nucstr, anum); 
02874 
02875     // Figure out if we are meta-stable or not
02876     std::string end_char = pyne::last_char(nucstr);
02877     if (end_char == "M")
02878       newnuc = (10000 * anum) + 1;
02879     else if (pyne::contains_substring(pyne::digits, end_char))
02880       newnuc = (10000 * anum);
02881     else
02882       throw NotANuclide(nucstr, newnuc);
02883 
02884     // Add the Z-number
02885     elem_name = pyne::remove_characters(nucstr.substr(0, nuclen-1), pyne::digits);
02886     elem_name = pyne::capitalize(elem_name);
02887     if (0 < name_zz.count(elem_name))
02888       newnuc = (10000000 * name_zz[elem_name]) + newnuc;
02889     else
02890       throw NotANuclide(nucstr, newnuc);
02891   } else {
02892     // Clearly not a nuclide
02893     throw NotANuclide(nuc, nucstr);
02894   }
02895   return newnuc;  
02896 };
02897

02899 /***************************/
02900 /*** iselement functions ***/
02901 /***************************/
02902 
02903 bool pyne::nucname::iselement(std::string nuc) {
02904   int n;
02905   try {
02906     n = id(nuc);
02907   }
02908   catch(NotANuclide) {
02909     return false;
02910   }
02911   return iselement(n);
02912 };
02913 
02914 bool pyne::nucname::iselement(const char * nuc) {
02915   return iselement(std::string(nuc));
02916 };
02917 
02918 bool pyne::nucname::iselement(int nuc) {
02919   int n;
02920   try {
02921     n = id(nuc);
02922   }
02923   catch(NotANuclide) {
02924     return false;
02925   }
02926  
02927   if (n <= 10000000)
02928     return false;
02929   int zzz = znum(n);
02930   int aaa = anum(n);
02931   if (zzz > 0 && aaa == 0)
02932     return true;  // is element
02933   return false;
02934 };

02936 /**********************/
02937 /*** name functions ***/
02938 /**********************/
02939 std::string pyne::nucname::name(int nuc) {
02940   int nucid = id(nuc);
02941   std::string newnuc = "";
02942 
02943   int zzz = nucid / 10000000;
02944   int ssss = nucid % 10000;
02945   int aaassss = nucid % 10000000;
02946   int aaa = aaassss / 10000;
02947 
02948   // Make sure the LL value is correct
02949   if (0 == zz_name.count(zzz))
02950     throw NotANuclide(nuc, nucid);
02951 
02952   // Add LL
02953   newnuc += zz_name[zzz];
02954 
02955   // Add A-number
02956   if (0 < aaa)
02957     newnuc += pyne::to_str(aaa);
02958 
02959   // Add meta-stable flag
02960   if (0 < ssss)
02961     newnuc += "M";
02962 
02963   return newnuc;
02964 };

02969   std::string newnuc (nuc);
02970   return name(newnuc);
02971 }

02974 std::string pyne::nucname::name(std::string nuc) {
02975   return name(id(nuc));
02976 }

03098 /*************************/
03099 /*** zzllaaam functions ***/
03100 /*************************/
03101 std::string pyne::nucname::zzllaaam(int nuc) {
03102   int nucid = id(nuc);
03103   std::string newnuc = "";
03104 
03105   int ssss = nucid % 10000;
03106   int aaassss = nucid % 10000000;
03107   int zzz = nucid / 10000000;
03108   int aaa = aaassss / 10000;
03109 
03110   // Make sure the LL value is correct
03111   if (0 == zz_name.count(zzz))
03112     throw NotANuclide(nuc, nucid);
03113   //Adding ZZ
03114   newnuc += pyne::to_str(zzz);
03115   newnuc += "-";
03116   // Add LL
03117   newnuc += zz_name[zzz];
03118   // Add required dash
03119   newnuc += "-";
03120   // Add AAA
03121   if (0 < aaassss)
03122     newnuc += pyne::to_str(aaa);
03123   // Add meta-stable flag
03124   if (0 < ssss)
03125     newnuc += "m";
03126   return newnuc;
03127 };

03138 };

03141 int pyne::nucname::zzllaaam_to_id(const char * nuc) {
03142   return zzllaaam_to_id(std::string(nuc));
03143 };
03144 
03145 
03146 int pyne::nucname::zzllaaam_to_id(std::string nuc) {
03147   if (nuc.empty())
03148     throw NotANuclide(nuc, "<empty>");
03149   int nucid;
03150   std::string elem_name;
03151 
03152   // Get the string into a regular form
03153   std::string nucstr = pyne::to_upper(nuc);
03154   // Removing first two characters (redundant), for 1 digit nuclides, such
03155   // as 2-He-4, the first slash will be removed, and the second attempt to
03156   // remove the second slash will do nothing.  
03157   nucstr.erase(0,2);
03158   nucstr = pyne::remove_substring(nucstr, "-");
03159   // Does nothing if nuclide is short, otherwise removes the second "-" instance
03160   nucstr = pyne::remove_substring(nucstr, "-");
03161   int nuclen = nucstr.length();
03162 
03163   // Nuclide is probably in name form, or some variation therein
03164   std::string anum_str = pyne::remove_characters(nucstr, pyne::alphabet);
03165 
03166   // natural element form, a la 'U' -> 920000000
03167   if (anum_str.empty() || pyne::contains_substring(nucstr, "NAT")) {
03168     elem_name = pyne::capitalize(pyne::remove_substring(nucstr, "NAT")); 
03169     if (0 < name_zz.count(elem_name))
03170       return 10000000 * name_zz[elem_name]; 
03171   }
03172   int anum = pyne::to_int(anum_str);
03173 
03174   // Figure out if we are meta-stable or not
03175   std::string end_char = pyne::last_char(nucstr);
03176   if (end_char == "M")
03177     nucid = (10000 * anum) + 1;
03178   else if (pyne::contains_substring(pyne::digits, end_char))
03179     nucid = (10000 * anum);
03180   else
03181     throw NotANuclide(nucstr, nucid);
03182 
03183   // Add the Z-number
03184   elem_name = pyne::remove_characters(nucstr.substr(0, nuclen-1), pyne::digits);
03185   elem_name = pyne::capitalize(elem_name);
03186   if (0 < name_zz.count(elem_name))
03187     nucid = (10000000 * name_zz[elem_name]) + nucid;
03188   else
03189     throw NotANuclide(nucstr, nucid);
03190   return nucid;
03191 };
03192 
03193 /**********************/
03194 /*** mcnp functions ***/
03195 /**********************/
03196 int pyne::nucname::mcnp(int nuc) {
03197   nuc = id(nuc);
03198   int ssss = nuc % 10000;
03199   int newnuc = nuc / 10000;
03200 
03201   // special case Am242(m)
03202   if (newnuc == 95242 && ssss < 2)
03203     ssss = (ssss + 1) % 2;
03204 
03205   // Handle the crazy MCNP meta-stable format
03206   if (0 != ssss && ssss < 10) 
03207     newnuc += 300 + (ssss * 100);
03208 
03209   return newnuc;
03210 };
03211 
03212 
03213 
03214 int pyne::nucname::mcnp(const char * nuc) {
03215   std::string newnuc (nuc);
03216   return mcnp(newnuc);
03217 };

03222   return mcnp(id(nuc));
03223 };
03224 
03225 //
03226 // MCNP -> id
03227 //
03228 int pyne::nucname::mcnp_to_id(int nuc) {
03229   int zzz = nuc / 1000;
03230   int aaa = nuc % 1000; 
03231   if (zzz == 0)
03232     throw NotANuclide(nuc, "not in the MCNP format");
03233   else if (zzz <= aaa) {
03234     if (aaa - 400 < 0) {
03235       if (nuc == 95242)
03236         return nuc * 10000 + 1;  // special case MCNP Am-242m
03237       else
03238         return nuc * 10000;  // Nuclide in normal MCNP form
03239     } else {
03240       // Nuclide in MCNP metastable form
03241       if (nuc == 95642)
03242         return (95642 - 400)*10000;  // special case MCNP Am-242
03243       nuc = ((nuc - 400) * 10000) + 1;
03244       while (3.0 < (float ((nuc/10000)%1000) / float (nuc/10000000)))
03245         nuc -= 999999;
03246       return nuc;
03247     }
03248   } else if (aaa == 0)
03249     // MCNP form natural nuclide
03250     return zzz * 10000000;
03251   throw IndeterminateNuclideForm(nuc, "");
03252 };
03253

03255 int pyne::nucname::mcnp_to_id(const char * nuc) {
03256   return mcnp_to_id(std::string(nuc));
03257 };
03258 
03259 
03260 int pyne::nucname::mcnp_to_id(std::string nuc) {
03261   return mcnp_to_id(pyne::to_int(nuc));
03262 };

03292 /*************************/
03293 /*** serpent functions ***/
03294 /*************************/
03295 std::string pyne::nucname::serpent(int nuc) {
03296   int nucid = id(nuc);
03297   std::string newnuc = "";
03298 
03299   int ssss = nucid % 10000;
03300   int aaassss = nucid % 10000000;
03301   int zzz = nucid / 10000000;
03302   int aaa = aaassss / 10000;
03303 
03304   // Make sure the LL value is correct
03305   if (0 == zz_name.count(zzz))
03306     throw NotANuclide(nuc, nucid);
03307 
03308   // Add LL
03309   std::string llupper = pyne::to_upper(zz_name[zzz]);
03310   std::string lllower = pyne::to_lower(zz_name[zzz]);
03311   newnuc += llupper[0];
03312   for (int l = 1; l < lllower.size(); l++)
03313     newnuc += lllower[l];  
03314 
03315   // Add required dash
03316   newnuc += "-";
03317 
03318   // Add A-number
03319   if (0 < aaassss)
03320     newnuc += pyne::to_str(aaa);
03321   else if (0 == aaassss)
03322     newnuc += "nat";
03323 
03324   // Add meta-stable flag
03325   if (0 < ssss)
03326     newnuc += "m";
03327 
03328   return newnuc;
03329 };
03330

03332 std::string pyne::nucname::serpent(const char * nuc) {
03333   std::string newnuc (nuc);
03334   return serpent(newnuc);
03335 };

03338 std::string pyne::nucname::serpent(std::string nuc) {
03339   return serpent(id(nuc));
03340 };

03342 //
03343 // Serpent -> id
03344 //
03345 //int pyne::nucname::serpent_to_id(int nuc)
03346 //{
03347 // Should be ZAID
03348 //};

03351 int pyne::nucname::serpent_to_id(const char * nuc) {
03352   return serpent_to_id(std::string(nuc));
03353 };
03354 
03355 
03356 int pyne::nucname::serpent_to_id(std::string nuc) {
03357   if (nuc.empty())
03358     throw NotANuclide(nuc, "<empty>");
03359   int nucid;
03360   std::string elem_name;
03361 
03362   // Get the string into a regular form
03363   std::string nucstr = pyne::to_upper(nuc);
03364   nucstr = pyne::remove_substring(nucstr, "-");
03365   int nuclen = nucstr.length();
03366 
03367   // Nuclide is probably in name form, or some variation therein
03368   std::string anum_str = pyne::remove_characters(nucstr, pyne::alphabet);
03369 
03370   // natural element form, a la 'U' -> 920000000
03371   if (anum_str.empty() || pyne::contains_substring(nucstr, "NAT")) {
03372     elem_name = pyne::capitalize(pyne::remove_substring(nucstr, "NAT")); 
03373     if (0 < name_zz.count(elem_name))
03374       return 10000000 * name_zz[elem_name]; 
03375   }
03376   int anum = pyne::to_int(anum_str);
03377 
03378   // Figure out if we are meta-stable or not
03379   std::string end_char = pyne::last_char(nucstr);
03380   if (end_char == "M")
03381     nucid = (10000 * anum) + 1;
03382   else if (pyne::contains_substring(pyne::digits, end_char))
03383     nucid = (10000 * anum);
03384   else
03385     throw NotANuclide(nucstr, nucid);
03386 
03387   // Add the Z-number
03388   elem_name = pyne::remove_characters(nucstr.substr(0, nuclen-1), pyne::digits);
03389   elem_name = pyne::capitalize(elem_name);
03390   if (0 < name_zz.count(elem_name))
03391     nucid = (10000000 * name_zz[elem_name]) + nucid;
03392   else
03393     throw NotANuclide(nucstr, nucid);
03394   return nucid;
03395 };
03396

03398 /**********************/
03399 /*** nist functions ***/
03400 /**********************/
03401 std::string pyne::nucname::nist(int nuc) {
03402   int nucid = id(nuc);
03403   std::string newnuc = "";
03404 
03405   int zzz = nucid / 10000000;
03406   int ssss = nucid % 10000;
03407   int aaassss = nucid % 10000000;
03408   int aaa = aaassss / 10000;
03409 
03410   // Make sure the LL value is correct
03411   if (0 == zz_name.count(zzz))
03412     throw NotANuclide(nuc, nucid);
03413 
03414   // Add A-number
03415   if (0 < aaassss)
03416     newnuc += pyne::to_str(aaa);
03417 
03418   // Add name
03419   std::string name_upper = pyne::to_upper(zz_name[zzz]);
03420   std::string name_lower = pyne::to_lower(zz_name[zzz]);
03421   newnuc += name_upper[0];
03422   for (int l = 1; l < name_lower.size(); l++)
03423     newnuc += name_lower[l];  
03424 
03425   // Add meta-stable flag
03426   // No metastable flag for NIST, 
03427   // but could add star, by uncommenting below
03428   //if (0 < mod_10)
03429   //  newnuc += "*";
03430 
03431   return newnuc;
03432 };

03457 
03458 int pyne::nucname::nist_to_id(std::string nuc) {
03459   if (nuc.empty())
03460     throw NotANuclide(nuc, "<empty>");
03461   int nucid;
03462   nuc = pyne::to_upper(nuc);
03463   std::string elem_name;
03464   int nuclen = nuc.length();
03465 
03466   // Nuclide is probably in name form, or some variation therein
03467   std::string anum_str = pyne::remove_characters(nuc, pyne::alphabet);
03468 
03469   // natural element form, a la 'U' -> 920000000
03470   if (anum_str.empty()) {
03471     elem_name = pyne::capitalize(nuc);
03472     if (0 < name_zz.count(elem_name))
03473       return 10000000 * name_zz[elem_name]; 
03474   }
03475   nucid = pyne::to_int(anum_str) * 10000;
03476 
03477   // Add the Z-number
03478   elem_name = pyne::remove_characters(nuc, pyne::digits);
03479   elem_name = pyne::capitalize(elem_name);
03480   if (0 < name_zz.count(elem_name))
03481     nucid = (10000000 * name_zz[elem_name]) + nucid;
03482   else
03483     throw NotANuclide(nuc, nucid);
03484   return nucid;
03485 };

03488 /************************/
03489 /*** cinder functions ***/
03490 /************************/
03491 int pyne::nucname::cinder(int nuc) {
03492   // cinder nuclides of form aaazzzm
03493   int nucid = id(nuc);
03494   int zzz = nucid / 10000000;
03495   int ssss = nucid % 10000;
03496   int aaassss = nucid % 10000000;
03497   int aaa = aaassss / 10000;
03498   if (10 <= ssss)
03499     ssss = 9;
03500   return (aaa*10000) + (zzz*10) + ssss;
03501 };

03518 //

03521   int aaazzz = nuc / 10;
03522   int zzz = aaazzz % 1000;
03523   int aaa = aaazzz / 1000;
03524   return (zzz * 10000000) + (aaa * 10000) + ssss;
03525 };

03540 /**********************/
03541 /*** ALARA functions ***/
03542 /**********************/
03543 std::string pyne::nucname::alara(int nuc) {
03544   int nucid = id(nuc);
03545   std::string newnuc = "";
03546   std::string ll = "";
03547 
03548   int zzz = nucid / 10000000;
03549   int ssss = nucid % 10000;
03550   int aaassss = nucid % 10000000;
03551   int aaa = aaassss / 10000;
03552 
03553   // Make sure the LL value is correct
03554   if (0 == zz_name.count(zzz))
03555     throw NotANuclide(nuc, nucid);
03556 
03557   // Add LL, in lower case
03558   ll += zz_name[zzz];
03559 
03560   for(int i = 0; ll[i] != '\0'; i++)
03561     ll[i] = tolower(ll[i]);
03562   newnuc += ll;
03563 
03564   // Add A-number
03565   if (0 < aaassss){
03566     newnuc += ":";
03567     newnuc += pyne::to_str(aaa);
03568   }
03569 
03570   // Note, ALARA input format does not use metastable flag
03571   return newnuc;
03572 };

03653 
03654 int pyne::nucname::sza_to_id(int nuc) {
03655   int sss = nuc / 1000000;
03656   int zzzaaa = nuc % 1000000;
03657   if (5 < sss){
03658   // Unphysical metastable state warning 
03659    warning("You have indicated a metastable state of " + pyne::to_str(sss) + ". Metastable state above 5, possibly unphysical. ");
03660   }
03661   return zzzaaa * 10000 + sss;
03662 }

03674 
03675 
03676 void pyne::nucname::_load_state_map(){
03677     for (int i = 0; i < TOTAL_STATE_MAPS; ++i) {
03678        state_id_map[map_nuc_ids[i]] = map_metastable[i];
03679     }
03680 }
03681 
03682 int pyne::nucname::state_id_to_id(int state) {
03683     int zzzaaa = (state / 10000) * 10000;
03684     int state_number = state % 10000;
03685     if (state_number == 0) return state;
03686     std::map<int, int>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end;
03687 
03688     nuc_iter = state_id_map.find(state);
03689     nuc_end = state_id_map.end();
03690     if (nuc_iter != nuc_end){ 
03691      int m = (*nuc_iter).second;
03692      return zzzaaa + m;
03693     }        
03694 
03695     if (state_id_map.empty())  {
03696       _load_state_map();
03697       return state_id_to_id(state);
03698     }
03699     throw IndeterminateNuclideForm(state, "no matching metastable state");
03700 }
03701 
03702 
03703 int pyne::nucname::id_to_state_id(int nuc_id) {
03704     int zzzaaa = (nuc_id / 10000) * 10000;
03705     int state = nuc_id % 10000;
03706     if (state == 0) return nuc_id;
03707     std::map<int, int>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end, it;
03708     
03709     nuc_iter = state_id_map.lower_bound(nuc_id);
03710     nuc_end = state_id_map.upper_bound(nuc_id + 10000);
03711     for (it = nuc_iter; it!= nuc_end; ++it){
03712         if (state == it->second) {
03713           return it->first;
03714         }
03715     }
03716     int m = (*nuc_iter).second;
03717     
03718     if (state_id_map.empty())  {
03719       _load_state_map();
03720       return id_to_state_id(nuc_id);
03721     }
03722     throw IndeterminateNuclideForm(state, "no matching state id");
03723 }

03730 // ENSDF  -> Id
03731 //
03732 
03733 int pyne::nucname::ensdf_to_id(const char * nuc) {

03735 };
03736 
03737 int pyne::nucname::ensdf_to_id(std::string nuc) {
03738   if (nuc.size() < 4) {
03739     return nucname::id(nuc);
03740   } else if (std::isdigit(nuc[3])) {
03741     int aaa = to_int(nuc.substr(0, 3));
03742     int zzz;
03743     std::string xx_str = nuc.substr(3,2); 
03744     zzz = to_int(xx_str) + 100;
03745     int nid = 10000 * aaa + 10000000 * zzz;
03746     return nid;
03747   } else {
03748     return nucname::id(nuc);
03749   }
03750   
03751 };

06080   // fill the maps

06150   // the following should be sorted by (dz, da, ds)
06151   // neutrons:
06152   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-4, -8))] = name_id["n2a"];
06153   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-4, -7))] = name_id["z_2a"];
06154   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -5))] = name_id["z_2na"];
06155   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -4))] = name_id["na"];

06157   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -4, 2))] = name_id["na_2"];
06158   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -3))] = name_id["a"];
06159   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -3, 1))] = name_id["a_1"];
06160   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -3, 2))] = name_id["a_2"];
06161   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -2))] = name_id["He3"];
06162   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -2, 1))] = name_id["He3_1"];
06163   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -2, 2))] = name_id["He3_2"];
06164   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -1))] = name_id["z_2p"];
06165   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -1, 1))] = name_id["z_2p_1"];
06166   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -1, 2))] = name_id["z_2p_2"];
06167   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, -3))] = name_id["nt"];
06168   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, -3, 1))] = name_id["nt_1"];
06169   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, -3, 2))] = name_id["nt_2"];
06170   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, -2))] = name_id["t"];
06171   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, -2, 1))] = name_id["t_1"];
06172   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, -2, 2))] = name_id["t_2"];
06173   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, -1))] = name_id["d"];
06174   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, -1, 1))] = name_id["d_1"];
06175   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, -1, 2))] = name_id["d_2"];
06176   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, 0))] = name_id["p"];
06177   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, 0, 1))] = name_id["p_1"];
06178   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, 0, 2))] = name_id["p_2"];
06179   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, -3))] = name_id["z_4n"];
06180   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, -3, 1))] = name_id["z_4n_1"];
06181   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, -2))] = name_id["z_3n"];
06182   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, -2, 1))] = name_id["z_3n_1"];
06183   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, -2, 2))] = name_id["z_3n_2"];
06184   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, -1))] = name_id["z_2n"];
06185   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, -1, 1))] = name_id["z_2n_1"];
06186   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, -1, 2))] = name_id["z_2n_2"];
06187   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, 0))] = name_id["scattering"];
06188   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, 0, 1))] = name_id["n_1"];
06189   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, 0, 2))] = name_id["n_2"];
06190   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, 1))] = name_id["absorption"];
06191   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, 1, 1))] = name_id["gamma_1"];
06192   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, 1, 2))] = name_id["gamma_2"];
06193   // proton:
06194   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(0, 0))] = name_id["scattering"];
06195   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(1, 1))] = name_id["absorption"];
06196   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(1, 0))] = name_id["n"];
06197   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(1, -1))] = name_id["z_2n"];
06198   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(1, -2))] = name_id["z_3n"];
06199   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(1, -3))] = name_id["z_4n"];
06200   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(-1, -1))] = name_id["z_2p"];
06201   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(0, -1))] = name_id["d"];
06202   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(0, -2))] = name_id["t"];
06203   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(-1, -2))] = name_id["He3"];
06204   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(-1, -3))] = name_id["a"];
06205   // deuterium:
06206   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(0, 0))] = name_id["scattering"];
06207   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(1, 2))] = name_id["absorption"];
06208   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(1, 1))] = name_id["n"];
06209   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(1, 0))] = name_id["z_2n"];
06210   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(1, -1))] = name_id["z_3n"];
06211   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(1, -2))] = name_id["z_4n"];
06212   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(0, 1))] = name_id["p"];
06213   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(-1, 0))] = name_id["z_2p"];
06214   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(0, -1))] = name_id["t"];
06215   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(-1, -1))] = name_id["He3"];
06216   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(-1, -2))] = name_id["a"];
06217   // tritium:
06218   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(0, 0))] = name_id["scattering"];
06219   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(1, 3))] = name_id["absorption"];
06220   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(1, 2))] = name_id["n"];
06221   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(1, 1))] = name_id["z_2n"];
06222   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(1, 0))] = name_id["z_3n"];
06223   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(1, -1))] = name_id["z_4n"];
06224   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(0, 2))] = name_id["p"];
06225   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(-1, 1))] = name_id["z_2p"];
06226   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(0, 1))] = name_id["d"];
06227   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(-1, 0))] = name_id["He3"];
06228   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(-1, -1))] = name_id["a"];
06229   // He3:
06230   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(0, 0))] = name_id["scattering"];
06231   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(2, 3))] = name_id["absorption"];
06232   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(2, 2))] = name_id["n"];
06233   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(2, 1))] = name_id["z_2n"];
06234   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(2, 0))] = name_id["z_3n"];
06235   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(2, -1))] = name_id["z_4n"];
06236   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(1, 2))] = name_id["p"];
06237   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(0, 1))] = name_id["z_2p"];
06238   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(1, 1))] = name_id["d"];
06239   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(1, 0))] = name_id["t"];
06240   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(0, -1))] = name_id["a"];
06241   // alpha:
06242   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(0, 0))] = name_id["scattering"];
06243   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(2, 4))] = name_id["absorption"];
06244   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(2, 3))] = name_id["n"];
06245   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(2, 2))] = name_id["z_2n"];
06246   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(2, 1))] = name_id["z_3n"];
06247   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(2, 0))] = name_id["z_4n"];
06248   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(1, 3))] = name_id["p"];
06249   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(0, 2))] = name_id["z_2p"];
06250   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(1, 2))] = name_id["d"];
06251   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(1, 1))] = name_id["t"];
06252   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(0, 1))] = name_id["He3"];
06253   // gamma:
06254   offset_id[make_pair("gamma", offset(0, -1))] = name_id["n"];
06255   offset_id[make_pair("gamma", offset(0, -2))] = name_id["z_2n"];
06256   offset_id[make_pair("gamma", offset(0, -3))] = name_id["z_3n"];
06257   offset_id[make_pair("gamma", offset(0, -4))] = name_id["z_4n"];
06258   offset_id[make_pair("gamma", offset(-1, -1))] = name_id["p"];
06259   offset_id[make_pair("gamma", offset(-2, -2))] = name_id["z_2p"];
06260   offset_id[make_pair("gamma", offset(-1, -2))] = name_id["d"];
06261   offset_id[make_pair("gamma", offset(-1, -3))] = name_id["t"];
06262   offset_id[make_pair("gamma", offset(-2, -3))] = name_id["He3"];
06263   offset_id[make_pair("gamma", offset(-2, -4))] = name_id["a"];
06264   // decay:
06265   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(0, -1))] = name_id["n"];
06266   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(0, -2))] = name_id["z_2n"];
06267   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(0, -3))] = name_id["z_3n"];
06268   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(0, -4))] = name_id["z_4n"];
06269   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-1, -1))] = name_id["p"];
06270   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-2, -2))] = name_id["z_2p"];
06271   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-1, -2))] = name_id["d"];
06272   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-1, -3))] = name_id["t"];
06273   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-2, -3))] = name_id["He3"];
06274   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-2, -4))] = name_id["a"];
06275   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(1, 0))] = name_id["bminus"];
06276   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-1, 0))] = name_id["bplus"];
06277   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(1, -1))] = name_id["bminus_n"];
06278   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-1, -4))] = name_id["bminus_a"];
06279   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(0, 0))] = name_id["it"];
06280   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-3, -4))] = name_id["bplus_a"];
06281   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-2, -1))] = name_id["bplus_p"];
06282   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(1, -2))] = name_id["bminus_2n"];
06283   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(1, -3))] = name_id["bminus_3n"];
06284   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(1, -4))] = name_id["bminus_4n"];
06285   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-3, -2))] = name_id["bplus_2p"];
06286   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-4, -3))] = name_id["bplus_3p"];
06287   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(2, 0))] = name_id["decay_2bminus"];
06288   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-2, 0))] = name_id["decay_2bplus"];
06289   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-6, -14))] = name_id["decay_14c"];
06290   
06291   // pre-loaded child offsets
06292   std::map<std::pair<std::string, int>, unsigned int>::iterator ioffid;
06293   for (ioffid = offset_id.begin(); ioffid != offset_id.end(); ioffid++) {
06294     id_offset[make_pair(ioffid->first.first, ioffid->second)] = ioffid->first.second;
06295   };
06296   // neutrons:
06297   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["nHe3"])] = offset(-2, -3);
06298   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["nHe3_1"])] = offset(-2, -3, 2);
06299   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["nHe3_2"])] = offset(-2, -3, 2);
06300   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["z_3np"])] = offset(-1, -3);
06301   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["nd"])] = offset(-1, -2);
06302   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["nd_1"])] = offset(-1, -2, 1);
06303   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["nd_2"])] = offset(-1, -2, 2);
06304   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["np"])] = offset(-1, -1);
06305   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["np_1"])] = offset(-1, -1, 1);
06306   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["np_2"])] = offset(-1, -1, 2);
06307   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["n"])] = offset(0, 0);
06308   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["gamma"])] = offset(0, 1);
06309   // decay:
06310   id_offset[make_pair("decay", name_id["bminus_p"])] = offset(0, -1);
06311   id_offset[make_pair("decay", name_id["ec_2p"])] = offset(-3, -2);
06312   id_offset[make_pair("decay", name_id["ec"])] = offset(-1, 0);
06313   id_offset[make_pair("decay", name_id["ec_bplus"])] = offset(-1, 0);
06314   id_offset[make_pair("decay", name_id["ecp"])] = offset(-2, -1);
06315   id_offset[make_pair("decay", name_id["eca"])] = offset(-3, -4);
06316   id_offset[make_pair("decay", name_id["decay_2ec"])] = offset(-2, 0);
06317   return NULL;
06318 };
06319 void * pyne::rxname::_ = pyne::rxname::_fill_maps();
06320 
06321 
06322 unsigned int pyne::rxname::hash(std::string s) {
06323   return pyne::rxname::hash(s.c_str());
06324   };
06325 
06326 unsigned int pyne::rxname::hash(const char * s) {
06327   // Modified from http://cboard.cprogramming.com/tech-board/114650-string-hashing-algorithm.html#post853145
06328   // starting from h = 32*2^5 > 1000, rather than 0, to reserve space for MT numbers
06329   int c;
06330   unsigned int h = 32; 
06331   while((c = *s++)) {
06332     h = ((h << 5) + h) ^ c;
06333   }
06334   return h;
06335 };
06336 
06337 
06338 // ************************
06339 // *** name functions *****
06340 // ************************
06341 
06342 std::string pyne::rxname::name(char * s) {
06343   return pyne::rxname::name(std::string(s));
06344   };
06345 
06346 std::string pyne::rxname::name(std::string s) {
06347   if (0 < names.count(s))
06348     return s;
06349   if (0 < altnames.count(s))
06350     return id_name[altnames[s]];
06351   // see if id in string form
06352   int i = 0;
06353   int I = s.length();
06354   int found = 0;
06355   while(0 <= found && i < I) {
06356     found = pyne::digits.find(s[i]);
06357     i++;
06358   }
06359   if (0<=found)
06360     return pyne::rxname::name(atoi(s.c_str()));
06361   // dead...
06362   throw NotAReaction(s, "???");
06363 };
06364 
06365 
06366 std::string pyne::rxname::name(int n) {
06367   return pyne::rxname::name((unsigned int) n);
06368 };
06369 
06370 std::string pyne::rxname::name(unsigned int n) {
06371   if (0 < id_name.count(n))
06372     return id_name[n];
06373   if (0 < mt_id.count(n))
06374     return id_name[mt_id[n]];
06375   throw NotAReaction(n, "???");
06376 };
06377 
06378 
06379 std::string pyne::rxname::name(int from_nuc, int to_nuc, std::string z) {
06380   // This assumes nuclides are in id form
06381   std::pair<std::string, int> key = std::make_pair(z, to_nuc - from_nuc);
06382   if (0 == offset_id.count(key))
06383     throw IndeterminateReactionForm("z=" + z + ", " + pyne::to_str(from_nuc) + \
06384                                     ", " + pyne::to_str(to_nuc), "???");
06385   return id_name[offset_id[key]];
06386 };
06387 
06388 std::string pyne::rxname::name(std::string from_nuc, int to_nuc, std::string z) {
06389   return pyne::rxname::name(pyne::nucname::id(from_nuc), 
06390                             pyne::nucname::id(to_nuc), z);
06391 };

06433   // This assumes nuclides are in id form

06435   if (0 == offset_id.count(key))
06436     throw IndeterminateReactionForm("z=" + z + ", " + pyne::to_str(from_nuc) + \
06437                                     ", " + pyne::to_str(to_nuc), "???");
06438   return offset_id[key];
06439 };

06590 // *** child functions ***
06591 // ***********************
06592 
06593 int pyne::rxname::child(int nuc, unsigned int rx, std::string z) {
06594   // This assumes nuclides are in id form
06595   std::pair<std::string, unsigned int> key = std::make_pair(z, rx);
06596   if (0 == id_offset.count(key))
06597     throw IndeterminateReactionForm("z=" + z + ", rx=" + pyne::to_str(rx), "???");
06598   int to_nuc = nuc + id_offset[key];
06599   if (!pyne::nucname::isnuclide(to_nuc))
06600     throw pyne::nucname::NotANuclide(nuc, to_nuc);
06601   return to_nuc;
06602 };
06603 
06604 int pyne::rxname::child(int nuc, std::string rx, std::string z) {
06605   return child(nuc, id(rx), z);
06606 };
06607 
06608 int pyne::rxname::child(std::string nuc, unsigned int rx, std::string z) {
06609   return child(pyne::nucname::id(nuc), rx, z);
06610 };
06611 
06612 int pyne::rxname::child(std::string nuc, std::string rx, std::string z) {
06613   return child(pyne::nucname::id(nuc), id(rx), z);
06614 };

06617 // ************************
06618 // *** parent functions ***
06619 // ************************
06620 
06621 int pyne::rxname::parent(int nuc, unsigned int rx, std::string z) {
06622   // This assumes nuclides are in id form
06623   std::pair<std::string, unsigned int> key = std::make_pair(z, rx);
06624   if (0 == id_offset.count(key))
06625     throw IndeterminateReactionForm("z=" + z + ", rx=" + pyne::to_str(rx), "???");
06626   int from_nuc = nuc - id_offset[key];
06627   if (!pyne::nucname::isnuclide(from_nuc))
06628     throw pyne::nucname::NotANuclide(from_nuc, nuc);
06629   return from_nuc;
06630 };
06631 
06632 int pyne::rxname::parent(int nuc, std::string rx, std::string z) {
06633   return parent(nuc, id(rx), z);
06634 };

06637   return parent(pyne::nucname::id(nuc), rx, z);
06638 };

06640 int pyne::rxname::parent(std::string nuc, std::string rx, std::string z) {
06641   return parent(pyne::nucname::id(nuc), id(rx), z);
06642 };

06692 /*****************************/
06693 /*** atomic_mass Functions ***/
06694 /*****************************/
06695 std::map<int, double> pyne::atomic_mass_map = std::map<int, double>();
06696 
06697 void pyne::_load_atomic_mass_map() {
06698   // Loads the important parts of atomic_wight table into atomic_mass_map
06699 
06700   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
06701   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
06702     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
06703 
06704   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
06705   if (!ish5)
06706     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
06707 
06708   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
06709   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(atomic_mass_data));
06710   H5Tinsert(desc, "nuc",   HOFFSET(atomic_mass_data, nuc),   H5T_NATIVE_INT);
06711   H5Tinsert(desc, "mass",  HOFFSET(atomic_mass_data, mass),  H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
06712   H5Tinsert(desc, "error", HOFFSET(atomic_mass_data, error), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
06713   H5Tinsert(desc, "abund", HOFFSET(atomic_mass_data, abund), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
06714 
06715   // Open the HDF5 file
06716   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY, H5P_DEFAULT);
06717 
06718   // Open the data set
06719   hid_t atomic_mass_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, "/atomic_mass", H5P_DEFAULT);
06720   hid_t atomic_mass_space = H5Dget_space(atomic_mass_set);
06721   int atomic_mass_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(atomic_mass_space);
06722 
06723   // Read in the data
06724   atomic_mass_data * atomic_mass_array = new atomic_mass_data[atomic_mass_length];
06725   H5Dread(atomic_mass_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT, atomic_mass_array);
06726 
06727   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
06728   H5Dclose(atomic_mass_set);
06729   H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
06730 
06731   // Ok now that we have the array of structs, put it in the map
06732   for(int n = 0; n < atomic_mass_length; n++) {
06733     atomic_mass_map.insert(std::pair<int, double>(atomic_mass_array[n].nuc, \
06734                                                   atomic_mass_array[n].mass));
06735     natural_abund_map.insert(std::pair<int, double>(atomic_mass_array[n].nuc, \
06736                                                     atomic_mass_array[n].abund));
06737   }
06738 
06739   delete[] atomic_mass_array;
06740 };
06741 
06742 
06743 double pyne::atomic_mass(int nuc) {
06744   // Find the nuclide's mass in AMU
06745   std::map<int, double>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end;
06746 
06747   nuc_iter = atomic_mass_map.find(nuc);
06748   nuc_end = atomic_mass_map.end();
06749 
06750   // First check if we already have the nuc mass in the map
06751   if (nuc_iter != nuc_end) {
06752     return (*nuc_iter).second;
06753   }
06754 
06755   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
06756   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
06757   if (atomic_mass_map.empty()) {
06758     // Don't fail if we can't load the library
06759     _load_atomic_mass_map();
06760     return atomic_mass(nuc);
06761   }
06762 
06763   double aw;
06764   int nucid = nucname::id(nuc);
06765 
06766   // If in an excited state, return the ground
06767   // state mass...not strictly true, but good guess.
06768   if (0 < nucid%10000) {
06769     aw = atomic_mass((nucid/10000)*10000);
06770     if (atomic_mass_map.count(nuc) != 1) {
06771       atomic_mass_map.insert(std::pair<int, double>(nuc, aw));
06772     }
06773     return aw;
06774   };
06775 
06776   // Finally, if none of these work,
06777   // take a best guess based on the
06778   // aaa number.
06779   aw = (double) ((nucid/10000)%1000);
06780   if (atomic_mass_map.count(nuc) != 1) {
06781     atomic_mass_map.insert(std::pair<int, double>(nuc, aw));
06782   }
06783   return aw;
06784 };
06785 
06786 
06787 double pyne::atomic_mass(char * nuc) {
06788   int nuc_zz = nucname::id(nuc);
06789   return atomic_mass(nuc_zz);
06790 };

06795   return atomic_mass(nuc_zz);

06799 /*******************************/
06800 /*** natural_abund functions ***/
06801 /*******************************/
06802 
06803 std::map<int, double> pyne::natural_abund_map = std::map<int, double>();
06804 
06805 double pyne::natural_abund(int nuc) {
06806   // Find the nuclide's natural abundance
06807   std::map<int, double>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end;
06808 
06809   nuc_iter = natural_abund_map.find(nuc);
06810   nuc_end = natural_abund_map.end();
06811 
06812   // First check if we already have the nuc mass in the map
06813   if (nuc_iter != nuc_end)
06814     return (*nuc_iter).second;
06815 
06816   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
06817   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
06818   if (natural_abund_map.empty()) {
06819     // Don't fail if we can't load the library
06820       _load_atomic_mass_map();
06821       return natural_abund(nuc);
06822   };
06823 
06824   double na;
06825   int nucid = nucname::id(nuc);
06826 
06827   // If in an excited state, return the ground
06828   // state abundance...not strictly true, but good guess.
06829   if (0 < nucid%10000) {
06830     na = natural_abund((nucid/10000)*10000);
06831     natural_abund_map[nuc] = na;
06832     return na;
06833   };
06834 
06835   // Finally, if none of these work,
06836   // take a best guess based on the
06837   // aaa number.
06838   na = 0.0;
06839   natural_abund_map[nuc] = na;
06840   return na;
06841 };
06842

06845   int nuc_zz = nucname::id(nuc);
06846   return natural_abund(nuc_zz);
06847 };

06857 /*************************/
06858 /*** Q_value Functions ***/
06859 /*************************/
06860 
06861 void pyne::_load_q_val_map() {
06862   // Loads the important parts of q_value table into q_value_map
06863 
06864   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
06865   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
06866     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
06867 
06868   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
06869   if (!ish5)
06870     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
06871 
06872   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
06873   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(q_val_data));
06874   H5Tinsert(desc, "nuc", HOFFSET(q_val_data, nuc),  H5T_NATIVE_INT);
06875   H5Tinsert(desc, "q_val", HOFFSET(q_val_data, q_val), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
06876   H5Tinsert(desc, "gamma_frac", HOFFSET(q_val_data, gamma_frac), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
06877 
06878   // Open the HDF5 file
06879   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY, H5P_DEFAULT);
06880 
06881   // Open the data set
06882   hid_t q_val_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, "/decay/q_values", H5P_DEFAULT);
06883   hid_t q_val_space = H5Dget_space(q_val_set);
06884   int q_val_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(q_val_space);
06885 
06886   // Read in the data
06887   q_val_data * q_val_array = new q_val_data[q_val_length];
06888   H5Dread(q_val_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT, q_val_array);
06889 
06890   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
06891   H5Dclose(q_val_set);
06892   H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
06893 
06894   // Ok now that we have the array of structs, put it in the map
06895   for(int n = 0; n < q_val_length; n++) {
06896     q_val_map[q_val_array[n].nuc] = q_val_array[n].q_val;
06897     gamma_frac_map[q_val_array[n].nuc] = q_val_array[n].gamma_frac;
06898   }
06899 
06900   delete[] q_val_array;
06901 };
06902 
06903 std::map<int, double> pyne::q_val_map = std::map<int, double>();
06904 
06905 double pyne::q_val(int nuc) {
06906   // Find the nuclide's q_val in MeV/fission
06907   std::map<int, double>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end;
06908 
06909   nuc_iter = q_val_map.find(nuc);
06910   nuc_end = q_val_map.end();
06911 
06912   // First check if we already have the nuc q_val in the map
06913   if (nuc_iter != nuc_end)
06914     return (*nuc_iter).second;
06915 
06916   // Next, fill up the map with values from the nuc_data.h5 if the map is empty.
06917   if (q_val_map.empty()) {
06918       _load_q_val_map();
06919       return q_val(nuc);
06920   };
06921 
06922   double qv;
06923   int nucid = nucname::id(nuc);
06924   if (nucid != nuc)
06925     return q_val(nucid);
06926 
06927   // If nuclide is not found, return 0
06928   qv = 0.0;
06929   q_val_map[nuc] = qv;
06930   return qv;
06931 };
06932 
06933 
06934 double pyne::q_val(const char * nuc) {
06935   int nuc_zz = nucname::id(nuc);
06936   return q_val(nuc_zz);
06937 };
06938 
06939 
06940 double pyne::q_val(std::string nuc) {
06941   int nuc_zz = nucname::id(nuc);
06942   return q_val(nuc_zz);
06943 };

06945 
06946 /****************************/
06947 /*** gamma_frac functions ***/
06948 /****************************/
06949 
06950 std::map<int, double> pyne::gamma_frac_map = std::map<int, double>();
06951 
06952 double pyne::gamma_frac(int nuc) {
06953   // Find the nuclide's fraction of Q that comes from gammas
06954   std::map<int, double>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end;
06955 
06956   nuc_iter = gamma_frac_map.find(nuc);
06957   nuc_end = gamma_frac_map.end();
06958 
06959   // First check if we already have the gamma_frac in the map
06960   if (nuc_iter != nuc_end)
06961     return (*nuc_iter).second;
06962 
06963   // Next, fill up the map with values from nuc_data.h5 if the map is empty.
06964   if (gamma_frac_map.empty()) {
06965       _load_q_val_map();
06966       return gamma_frac(nuc);
06967   };
06968 
06969   double gf;
06970   int nucid = nucname::id(nuc);
06971   if (nucid != nuc)
06972     return gamma_frac(nucid);
06973 
06974   // If nuclide is not found, return 0
06975   gf = 0.0;
06976   gamma_frac_map[nucid] = gf;
06977   return gf;
06978 };
06979 
06980 
06981 double pyne::gamma_frac(const char * nuc) {
06982   int nuc_zz = nucname::id(nuc);
06983   return gamma_frac(nuc_zz);
06984 };
06985 
06986 
06987 double pyne::gamma_frac(std::string nuc) {
06988   int nuc_zz = nucname::id(nuc);
06989   return gamma_frac(nuc_zz);
06990 };

06993 /*****************************/
06994 /*** Dose Factor Functions ***/
06995 /*****************************/
06996 /***************************************************************************
06997 This data is from: [Exposure Scenarios and Unit Dose Factors for the Hanford
06998 Immobilized Low-Activity Tank Waste Performance Assessment, ref.
06999 HNF-SD-WM-TI-707 Rev. 1 December 1999] Appendix O of HNF-5636 [DATA PACKAGES
07000 FOR THE HANFORD IMMOBILIZED LOW-ACTIVITY TANK WASTE PERFORMANCE ASSESSMENT:
07001 2001 VERSION]
07002 
07003 Liability Disclaimer: The PyNE Development Team shall not be liable for any
07004 loss or injury resulting from decisions made with this data.
07005 **************************************************************************/
07006 
07007 void pyne::_load_dose_map(std::map<int, dose>& dm, std::string source_path) {
07008   herr_t status;
07009 
07010   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
07011   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
07012     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
07013 
07014   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
07015   if (!ish5)
07016     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
07017 
07018   // Defining string type for lung model data
07019   hid_t string_type_;
07020   string_type_ = H5Tcopy(H5T_C_S1);
07021   H5Tset_size(string_type_, 1);
07022   H5Tset_strpad(string_type_, H5T_STR_NULLPAD);
07023 
07024   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
07025   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(dose));
07026   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "nuc", HOFFSET(dose, nuc), H5T_NATIVE_INT);
07027   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ext_air_dose", HOFFSET(dose, ext_air_dose), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07028   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ratio", HOFFSET(dose, ratio), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07029   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ext_soil_dose", HOFFSET(dose, ext_soil_dose), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07030   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ingest_dose", HOFFSET(dose, ingest_dose), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07031   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "fluid_frac", HOFFSET(dose, fluid_frac), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07032   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "inhale_dose", HOFFSET(dose, inhale_dose), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07033   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "lung_mod", HOFFSET(dose, lung_mod), string_type_);
07034 
07035   // Open the HDF5 file
07036   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY, H5P_DEFAULT);
07037 
07038   // Convert source_path to proper format for HD5open
07039   const char * c = source_path.c_str();
07040 
07041   // Open the data set
07042   hid_t dose_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, c, H5P_DEFAULT);
07043   hid_t dose_space = H5Dget_space(dose_set);
07044   int dose_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(dose_space);
07045 
07046   // Read in the data
07047   dose * dose_array = new dose[dose_length];
07048   H5Dread(dose_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT, dose_array);
07049 
07050   // Put array of structs in the map
07051   for (int n = 0; n < dose_length; n++) {
07052     dm[dose_array[n].nuc] = dose_array[n];
07053   };
07054 
07055   // Close the nuc_data library
07056   H5Dclose(dose_set);
07057   H5Tclose(string_type_);
07058   H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
07059 
07060   delete[] dose_array;
07061 };
07062 
07063 ///
07064 /// Functions for Source Location in nuc_data.h5
07065 /// and related Map Pointers
07066 ///
07067 
07068 std::string source_string(int source) {
07069   std::string source_location;
07070   if (source == 1) {
07071     source_location = "/dose_factors/DOE";
07072   } else if (source == 2) {
07073     source_location = "/dose_factors/GENII";
07074   } else {
07075     source_location = "/dose_factors/EPA";
07076   }
07077   return source_location;
07078 };
07079 
07080 std::map<int, pyne::dose>& dose_source_map(int source) {
07081   std::map<int, pyne::dose>* dm;
07082   if (source == 1) {
07083     dm = &pyne::doe_dose_map;
07084   } else if (source == 2) {
07085     dm = &pyne::genii_dose_map;
07086   } else {
07087     dm = &pyne::epa_dose_map;
07088   }
07089   if (dm->empty()) {
07090       std::string source_path = source_string(source);
07091       _load_dose_map(*dm, source_path);
07092   }
07093   return *dm;
07094 };
07095 
07096 std::map<int, pyne::dose> pyne::epa_dose_map;
07097 std::map<int, pyne::dose> pyne::doe_dose_map;
07098 std::map<int, pyne::dose> pyne::genii_dose_map;
07099

07279 
07280 /***********************************/
07281 /*** scattering length functions ***/
07282 /***********************************/
07283 std::map<int, xd_complex_t> pyne::b_coherent_map = std::map<int, xd_complex_t>();
07284 std::map<int, xd_complex_t> pyne::b_incoherent_map = std::map<int, xd_complex_t>();
07285 std::map<int, double> pyne::b_map = std::map<int, double>();
07286 
07287 
07288 void pyne::_load_scattering_lengths() {
07289   // Loads the important parts of atomic_wight table into atomic_mass_map
07290   herr_t status;
07291 
07292   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
07293   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
07294     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
07295 
07296   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
07297   if (!ish5)
07298     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
07299 
07300   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
07301   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(scattering_lengths));
07302   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "nuc", HOFFSET(scattering_lengths, nuc), H5T_NATIVE_INT);
07303   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "b_coherent", HOFFSET(scattering_lengths, b_coherent),
07304                       h5wrap::PYTABLES_COMPLEX128);
07305   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "b_incoherent", HOFFSET(scattering_lengths, b_incoherent),
07306                       h5wrap::PYTABLES_COMPLEX128);
07307   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "xs_coherent", HOFFSET(scattering_lengths, xs_coherent),
07308                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07309   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "xs_incoherent", HOFFSET(scattering_lengths, xs_incoherent),
07310                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07311   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "xs", HOFFSET(scattering_lengths, xs), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07312 
07313   // Open the HDF5 file
07314   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY, H5P_DEFAULT);
07315 
07316   // Open the data set
07317   hid_t scat_len_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, "/neutron/scattering_lengths", H5P_DEFAULT);
07318   hid_t scat_len_space = H5Dget_space(scat_len_set);
07319   int scat_len_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(scat_len_space);
07320 
07321   // Read in the data
07322   scattering_lengths * scat_len_array = new scattering_lengths[scat_len_length];
07323   status = H5Dread(scat_len_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT, scat_len_array);
07324 
07325   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
07326   status = H5Dclose(scat_len_set);
07327   status = H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
07328 
07329   // Ok now that we have the array of stucts, put it in the maps
07330   for(int n = 0; n < scat_len_length; n++) {
07331     b_coherent_map[scat_len_array[n].nuc] = scat_len_array[n].b_coherent;
07332     b_incoherent_map[scat_len_array[n].nuc] = scat_len_array[n].b_incoherent;
07333   };
07334 
07335   delete[] scat_len_array;
07336 };
07337 
07338 
07339 
07340 //
07341 // Coherent functions
07342 //
07343 
07344 
07345 xd_complex_t pyne::b_coherent(int nuc) {
07346   // Find the nuclide's bound scattering length in cm
07347   std::map<int, xd_complex_t>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end;
07348 
07349   nuc_iter = b_coherent_map.find(nuc);
07350   nuc_end = b_coherent_map.end();
07351 
07352   // First check if we already have the nuc in the map
07353   if (nuc_iter != nuc_end)
07354     return (*nuc_iter).second;
07355 
07356   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
07357   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
07358   if (b_coherent_map.empty()) {
07359     _load_scattering_lengths();
07360     return b_coherent(nuc);
07361   };
07362 
07363   xd_complex_t bc;
07364   int nucid = nucname::id(nuc);
07365   int znum = nucname::znum(nucid);
07366   int anum = nucname::anum(nucid);
07367 
07368   // Try to find a nuclide with matching A-number
07369   nuc_iter = b_coherent_map.begin();
07370   while (nuc_iter != nuc_end) {
07371     if (anum == nucname::anum((*nuc_iter).first)) {
07372       bc = (*nuc_iter).second;
07373       b_coherent_map[nuc] = bc;
07374       return bc;
07375     };
07376     nuc_iter++;
07377   };
07378 
07379   // Try to find a nuclide with matching Z-number
07380   nuc_iter = b_coherent_map.begin();
07381   while (nuc_iter != nuc_end) {
07382     if (znum == nucname::znum((*nuc_iter).first)) {
07383       bc = (*nuc_iter).second;
07384       b_coherent_map[nuc] = bc;
07385       return bc;
07386     };
07387     nuc_iter++;
07388   };
07389 
07390   // Finally, if none of these work,
07391   // just return zero...
07392   bc.re = 0.0;
07393   bc.im = 0.0;
07394   b_coherent_map[nuc] = bc;
07395   return bc;
07396 };
07397 
07398 
07399 xd_complex_t pyne::b_coherent(char * nuc) {
07400   int nuc_zz = nucname::id(nuc);
07401   return b_coherent(nuc_zz);
07402 };
07403 
07404 
07405 xd_complex_t pyne::b_coherent(std::string nuc) {
07406   int nuc_zz = nucname::id(nuc);
07407   return b_coherent(nuc_zz);
07408 };
07409 
07410 
07411 
07412 //
07413 // Incoherent functions
07414 //
07415 
07416 
07417 xd_complex_t pyne::b_incoherent(int nuc) {
07418   // Find the nuclide's bound inchoherent scattering length in cm
07419   std::map<int, xd_complex_t>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end;
07420 
07421   nuc_iter = b_incoherent_map.find(nuc);
07422   nuc_end = b_incoherent_map.end();
07423 
07424   // First check if we already have the nuc in the map
07425   if (nuc_iter != nuc_end)
07426     return (*nuc_iter).second;
07427 
07428   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
07429   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
07430   if (b_incoherent_map.empty()) {
07431     _load_scattering_lengths();
07432     return b_incoherent(nuc);
07433   };
07434 
07435   xd_complex_t bi;
07436   int nucid = nucname::id(nuc);
07437   int znum = nucname::znum(nucid);
07438   int anum = nucname::anum(nucid);
07439 
07440   // Try to find a nuclide with matching A-number
07441   nuc_iter = b_incoherent_map.begin();
07442   while (nuc_iter != nuc_end) {
07443     if (anum == nucname::anum((*nuc_iter).first)) {
07444       bi = (*nuc_iter).second;
07445       b_incoherent_map[nuc] = bi;
07446       return bi;
07447     };
07448     nuc_iter++;
07449   };
07450 
07451   // Try to find a nuclide with matching Z-number
07452   nuc_iter = b_incoherent_map.begin();
07453   while (nuc_iter != nuc_end) {
07454     if (znum == nucname::znum((*nuc_iter).first)) {
07455       bi = (*nuc_iter).second;
07456       b_incoherent_map[nuc] = bi;
07457       return bi;
07458     };
07459     nuc_iter++;
07460   };
07461 
07462   // Finally, if none of these work,
07463   // just return zero...
07464   bi.re = 0.0;
07465   bi.im = 0.0;
07466   b_incoherent_map[nuc] = bi;
07467   return bi;
07468 };
07469 
07470 
07471 xd_complex_t pyne::b_incoherent(char * nuc) {
07472   return b_incoherent(nucname::id(nuc));
07473 };
07474 
07475 
07476 xd_complex_t pyne::b_incoherent(std::string nuc) {
07477   return b_incoherent(nucname::id(nuc));
07478 };
07479 
07480 
07481 
07482 //
07483 // b functions
07484 //
07485 
07486 double pyne::b(int nuc) {
07487   // Find the nuclide's bound scattering length in cm
07488   std::map<int, double>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end;
07489 
07490   nuc_iter = b_map.find(nuc);
07491   nuc_end = b_map.end();
07492 
07493   // First check if we already have the nuc in the map
07494   if (nuc_iter != nuc_end)
07495     return (*nuc_iter).second;
07496 
07497   // Next, calculate the value from coherent and incoherent lengths
07498   xd_complex_t bc = b_coherent(nuc);
07499   xd_complex_t bi = b_incoherent(nuc);
07500 
07501   double b_val = sqrt(bc.re*bc.re + bc.im*bc.im + bi.re*bi.re + bi.im*bi.im);
07502 
07503   return b_val;
07504 };
07505 
07506 
07507 double pyne::b(char * nuc) {
07508   int nucid = nucname::id(nuc);
07509   return b(nucid);
07510 };
07511 
07512 
07513 double pyne::b(std::string nuc) {
07514   int nucid = nucname::id(nuc);
07515   return b(nucid);
07516 };

07519 
07520 //
07521 // Fission Product Yield Data
07522 //
07523 std::map<std::pair<int, int>, double> pyne::wimsdfpy_data = \
07524   std::map<std::pair<int, int>, double>();
07525 
07526 void pyne::_load_wimsdfpy() {
07527   herr_t status;
07528 
07529   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
07530   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
07531     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
07532 
07533   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
07534   if (!ish5)
07535     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
07536 
07537   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
07538   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(wimsdfpy));
07539   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "from_nuc", HOFFSET(wimsdfpy, from_nuc),
07540                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
07541   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "to_nuc", HOFFSET(wimsdfpy, to_nuc),
07542                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
07543   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "yields", HOFFSET(wimsdfpy, yields),
07544                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07545 
07546   // Open the HDF5 file
07547   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY,
07548                               H5P_DEFAULT);
07549 
07550   // Open the data set
07551   hid_t wimsdfpy_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, "/neutron/wimsd_fission_products",
07552                                 H5P_DEFAULT);
07553   hid_t wimsdfpy_space = H5Dget_space(wimsdfpy_set);
07554   int wimsdfpy_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(wimsdfpy_space);
07555 
07556   // Read in the data
07557   wimsdfpy * wimsdfpy_array = new wimsdfpy[wimsdfpy_length];
07558   status = H5Dread(wimsdfpy_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT, wimsdfpy_array);
07559 
07560   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
07561   status = H5Dclose(wimsdfpy_set);
07562   status = H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
07563 
07564   // Ok now that we have the array of stucts, put it in the maps
07565   for(int n=0; n < wimsdfpy_length; n++) {
07566     wimsdfpy_data[std::make_pair(wimsdfpy_array[n].from_nuc,
07567       wimsdfpy_array[n].to_nuc)] = wimsdfpy_array[n].yields;
07568   };
07569 
07570   delete[] wimsdfpy_array;
07571 };
07572 
07573 
07574 std::map<std::pair<int, int>, pyne::ndsfpysub> pyne::ndsfpy_data = \
07575   std::map<std::pair<int, int>, pyne::ndsfpysub>();
07576 
07577 void pyne::_load_ndsfpy() {
07578   herr_t status;
07579 
07580   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
07581   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
07582     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
07583 
07584   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
07585   if (!ish5)
07586     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
07587 
07588   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
07589   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(ndsfpy));
07590   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "from_nuc", HOFFSET(ndsfpy, from_nuc),
07591                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
07592   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "to_nuc", HOFFSET(ndsfpy, to_nuc),
07593                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
07594   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "yield_thermal", HOFFSET(ndsfpy, yield_thermal),
07595                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07596   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "yield_thermal_err", HOFFSET(ndsfpy, yield_thermal_err),
07597                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07598   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "yield_fast", HOFFSET(ndsfpy, yield_fast),
07599                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07600   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "yield_fast_err", HOFFSET(ndsfpy, yield_fast_err),
07601                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07602   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "yield_14MeV", HOFFSET(ndsfpy, yield_14MeV),
07603                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07604   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "yield_14MeV_err", HOFFSET(ndsfpy, yield_14MeV_err),
07605                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07606 
07607   // Open the HDF5 file
07608   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY,
07609                               H5P_DEFAULT);
07610 
07611   // Open the data set
07612   hid_t ndsfpy_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, "/neutron/nds_fission_products",
07613                                 H5P_DEFAULT);
07614   hid_t ndsfpy_space = H5Dget_space(ndsfpy_set);
07615   int ndsfpy_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(ndsfpy_space);
07616 
07617   // Read in the data
07618   ndsfpy * ndsfpy_array = new ndsfpy[ndsfpy_length];
07619   status = H5Dread(ndsfpy_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT, ndsfpy_array);
07620 
07621   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
07622   status = H5Dclose(ndsfpy_set);
07623   status = H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
07624 
07625   ndsfpysub ndsfpysub_temp;
07626 
07627   // Ok now that we have the array of structs, put it in the maps
07628   for(int n=0; n < ndsfpy_length; n++) {
07629     ndsfpysub_temp.yield_thermal = ndsfpy_array[n].yield_thermal;
07630     ndsfpysub_temp.yield_thermal_err = ndsfpy_array[n].yield_thermal_err;
07631     ndsfpysub_temp.yield_fast = ndsfpy_array[n].yield_fast;
07632     ndsfpysub_temp.yield_fast_err = ndsfpy_array[n].yield_fast_err;
07633     ndsfpysub_temp.yield_14MeV = ndsfpy_array[n].yield_14MeV;
07634     ndsfpysub_temp.yield_14MeV_err = ndsfpy_array[n].yield_14MeV_err;
07635     ndsfpy_data[std::make_pair(ndsfpy_array[n].from_nuc,
07636       ndsfpy_array[n].to_nuc)] = ndsfpysub_temp;
07637   };
07638 
07639 
07640 
07641   delete[] ndsfpy_array;
07642 };
07643 
07644 double pyne::fpyield(std::pair<int, int> from_to, int source, bool get_error) {
07645   // Note that this may be expanded eventually to include other
07646   // sources of fission product data.
07647 
07648   // Find the parent/child pair branch ratio as a fraction
07649   if (source == 0) {
07650     std::map<std::pair<int, int>, double>::iterator fpy_iter, fpy_end;
07651     fpy_iter = wimsdfpy_data.find(from_to);
07652     fpy_end = wimsdfpy_data.end();
07653     if (fpy_iter != fpy_end)
07654         //if (get_error == true) return 0;
07655         return (*fpy_iter).second;
07656   } else {
07657     std::map<std::pair<int, int>, ndsfpysub>::iterator fpy_iter, fpy_end;
07658     fpy_iter = ndsfpy_data.find(from_to);
07659     fpy_end = ndsfpy_data.end();
07660     if (fpy_iter != fpy_end) {
07661         switch (source) {
07662           case 1:
07663             if (get_error)
07664                 return (*fpy_iter).second.yield_thermal_err;
07665             return (*fpy_iter).second.yield_thermal;
07666             break;
07667           case 2:
07668             if (get_error)
07669                 return (*fpy_iter).second.yield_fast_err;
07670             return (*fpy_iter).second.yield_fast;
07671             break;
07672           case 3:
07673             if (get_error)
07674                 return (*fpy_iter).second.yield_14MeV_err;
07675             return (*fpy_iter).second.yield_14MeV;
07676             break;
07677         }
07678     }
07679   }
07680 
07681 
07682   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
07683   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
07684   if ((source == 0 ) && (wimsdfpy_data.empty())) {
07685     _load_wimsdfpy();
07686     return fpyield(from_to, 0, get_error);
07687   }else if (ndsfpy_data.empty()) {
07688     _load_ndsfpy();
07689     return fpyield(from_to, source, get_error);
07690   }
07691 
07692   // Finally, if none of these work,
07693   // assume the value is stable
07694   double fpy = 0.0;
07695   wimsdfpy_data[from_to] = fpy;
07696   return fpy;
07697 };
07698 
07699 double pyne::fpyield(int from_nuc, int to_nuc, int source, bool get_error) {
07700   return fpyield(std::pair<int, int>(nucname::id(from_nuc),
07701                                      nucname::id(to_nuc)), source, get_error);
07702 };
07703 
07704 double pyne::fpyield(char * from_nuc, char * to_nuc, int source, bool get_error) {
07705   return fpyield(std::pair<int, int>(nucname::id(from_nuc),
07706                                      nucname::id(to_nuc)), source, get_error);
07707 };
