07709 double pyne::fpyield(std::string from_nuc, std::string to_nuc, int source,
07710                      bool get_error) {
07711   return fpyield(std::pair<int, int>(nucname::id(from_nuc),
07712                                      nucname::id(to_nuc)), source, get_error);
07713 };

07720 //
07721 // Data access tools
07722 //
07723 
07724 bool pyne::swapmapcompare::operator()(const std::pair<int, double>& lhs,
07725 const std::pair<int, double>& rhs) const {
07726     return lhs.second<rhs.second || (!(rhs.second<lhs.second) &&
07727       lhs.first<rhs.first);
07728 };
07729 
07730 template<typename T, typename U> std::vector<T> pyne::data_access(
07731 double energy_min, double energy_max, size_t valoffset, std::map<std::pair<int,
07732 double>, U>  &data) {
07733   typename std::map<std::pair<int, double>, U, swapmapcompare>::iterator
07734     nuc_iter, nuc_end, it;
07735   std::map<std::pair<int, double>, U, swapmapcompare> dc(data.begin(),
07736     data.end());
07737   std::vector<T> result;
07738   if (energy_max < energy_min){
07739     double temp = energy_max;
07740     energy_max = energy_min;
07741     energy_min = temp;
07742   }
07743   nuc_iter = dc.lower_bound(std::make_pair(0, energy_min));
07744   nuc_end = dc.upper_bound(std::make_pair(9999999999, energy_max));
07745   T *ret;
07746   // First check if we already have the nuc in the map
07747   for (it = nuc_iter; it!= nuc_end; ++it){
07748     ret = (T *)((char *)&(it->second) + valoffset);
07749     result.push_back(*ret);
07750   }
07751   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
07752   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
07753   if (data.empty())
07754   {
07755     _load_data<U>();
07756     return data_access<T, U>(energy_min, energy_max, valoffset, data);
07757   };
07758   return result;
07759 };
07760 
07761 template<typename T, typename U> std::vector<T> pyne::data_access(int parent,
07762 double min, double max, size_t valoffset,
07763 std::map<std::pair<int, double>, U>  &data) {
07764   typename std::map<std::pair<int, double>, U>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end, it;
07765   std::vector<T> result;
07766   nuc_iter = data.lower_bound(std::make_pair(parent,min));
07767   nuc_end = data.upper_bound(std::make_pair(parent,max));
07768   T *ret;
07769   // First check if we already have the nuc in the map
07770   for (it = nuc_iter; it!= nuc_end; ++it){
07771     ret = (T *)((char *)&(it->second) + valoffset);
07772     result.push_back(*ret);
07773   }
07774   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
07775   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
07776   if (data.empty())
07777   {
07778     _load_data<U>();
07779     return data_access<T, U>(parent, min, max, valoffset, data);
07780   };
07781   return result;
07782 };
07783 
07784 template<typename T, typename U> T pyne::data_access(std::pair<int, int>
07785 from_to, size_t valoffset, std::map<std::pair<int, int>, U> &data) {
07786   typename std::map<std::pair<int, int>, U>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end;
07787 
07788   nuc_iter = data.find(from_to);
07789   nuc_end = data.end();
07790   T *ret;
07791   // First check if we already have the nuc in the map
07792   if (nuc_iter != nuc_end){
07793     ret = (T *)((char *)&(nuc_iter->second) + valoffset);
07794     return *ret;
07795   }
07796   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
07797   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
07798   if (data.empty())
07799   {
07800     _load_data<U>();
07801     return data_access<T, U>(from_to, valoffset, data);
07802   };
07803   // This is okay for now because we only return ints and doubles
07804   return 0;
07805 }
07806 
07807 template<typename T, typename U> std::vector<T> pyne::data_access(int parent,
07808 size_t valoffset, std::map<std::pair<int, int>, U> &data){
07809   typename std::map<std::pair<int, int>, U>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end, it;
07810   std::vector<T> result;
07811   nuc_iter = data.lower_bound(std::make_pair(parent,0));
07812   nuc_end = data.upper_bound(std::make_pair(parent,9999999999));
07813   T *ret;
07814   // First check if we already have the nuc in the map
07815   for (it = nuc_iter; it!= nuc_end; ++it){
07816     ret = (T *)((char *)&(it->second) + valoffset);
07817     result.push_back(*ret);
07818   }
07819   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
07820   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
07821   if (data.empty())
07822   {
07823     _load_data<U>();
07824     return data_access<T, U>(parent, valoffset, data);
07825   };
07826   return result;
07827 };
07828 
07829 template<typename T, typename U> std::vector<T> pyne::data_access(int parent,
07830 size_t valoffset, std::map<std::pair<int, unsigned int>, U> &data){
07831   typename std::map<std::pair<int, unsigned int>, U>::iterator nuc_iter,
07832    nuc_end, it;
07833   std::vector<T> result;
07834   nuc_iter = data.lower_bound(std::make_pair(parent,0));
07835   nuc_end = data.upper_bound(std::make_pair(parent,UINT_MAX));
07836   T *ret;
07837   // First check if we already have the nuc in the map
07838   for (it = nuc_iter; it!= nuc_end; ++it){
07839     ret = (T *)((char *)&(it->second) + valoffset);
07840     result.push_back(*ret);
07841   }
07842   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
07843   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
07844   if (data.empty())
07845   {
07846     _load_data<U>();
07847     return data_access<T, U>(parent, valoffset, data);
07848   };
07849   return result;
07850 };
07851 
07852 template<typename U> double pyne::data_access(int nuc,
07853 size_t valoffset, std::map<int, U> &data){
07854   typename std::map<int, U>::iterator nuc_iter,
07855    nuc_end;
07856   nuc_iter = data.find(nuc);
07857   nuc_end = data.end();
07858   // First check if we already have the nuc in the map
07859   if (nuc_iter != nuc_end){
07860     return *(double *)((char *)&(nuc_iter->second) + valoffset);
07861   }
07862   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
07863   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
07864   if (data.empty())
07865   {
07866     _load_data<U>();
07867     return data_access<U>(nuc, valoffset, data);
07868   };
07869   throw pyne::nucname::NotANuclide(nuc, "");
07870 };

07872 
07873 //
07874 // Load atomic data
07875 //
07876 
07877 std::map<int, pyne::atomic> pyne::atomic_data_map;
07878 
07879 template<> void pyne::_load_data<pyne::atomic>() {
07880   // Loads the atomic table into memory
07881   herr_t status;
07882 
07883   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
07884   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
07885     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
07886 
07887   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
07888   if (!ish5)
07889     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
07890 
07891   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
07892   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(atomic));
07893   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "z", HOFFSET(atomic, z),
07894                       H5T_NATIVE_INT);
07895   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "k_shell_fluor", HOFFSET(atomic, k_shell_fluor),
07896                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07897   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "k_shell_fluor_error", HOFFSET(atomic, k_shell_fluor_error),
07898                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07899   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "l_shell_fluor", HOFFSET(atomic, l_shell_fluor),
07900                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07901   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "l_shell_fluor_error", HOFFSET(atomic, l_shell_fluor_error),
07902                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07903   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "prob", HOFFSET(atomic, prob),
07904                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07905   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "k_shell_be", HOFFSET(atomic, k_shell_be),
07906                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07907   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "k_shell_be_err", HOFFSET(atomic, k_shell_be_err),
07908                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07909   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "li_shell_be", HOFFSET(atomic, li_shell_be),
07910                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07911   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "li_shell_be_err", HOFFSET(atomic, li_shell_be_err),
07912                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07913   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "mi_shell_be", HOFFSET(atomic, mi_shell_be),
07914                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07915   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "mi_shell_be_err", HOFFSET(atomic, mi_shell_be_err),
07916                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07917   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ni_shell_be", HOFFSET(atomic, ni_shell_be),
07918                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07919   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ni_shell_be_err", HOFFSET(atomic, ni_shell_be_err),
07920                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07921   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "kb_to_ka", HOFFSET(atomic, kb_to_ka),
07922                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07923   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "kb_to_ka_err", HOFFSET(atomic, kb_to_ka_err),
07924                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07925   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ka2_to_ka1", HOFFSET(atomic, ka2_to_ka1),
07926                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07927   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ka2_to_ka1_err", HOFFSET(atomic, ka2_to_ka1_err),
07928                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07929   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "l_auger", HOFFSET(atomic, l_auger),
07930                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07931   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "k_auger", HOFFSET(atomic, k_auger),
07932                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07933   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ka1_x_ray_en", HOFFSET(atomic, ka1_x_ray_en),
07934                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07935   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ka1_x_ray_en_err", HOFFSET(atomic, ka1_x_ray_en_err),
07936                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07937   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ka2_x_ray_en", HOFFSET(atomic, ka2_x_ray_en),
07938                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07939   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ka2_x_ray_en_err", HOFFSET(atomic, ka2_x_ray_en_err),
07940                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07941   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "kb_x_ray_en", HOFFSET(atomic, kb_x_ray_en),
07942                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07943   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "l_x_ray_en", HOFFSET(atomic, l_x_ray_en),
07944                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07945 
07946   // Open the HDF5 file
07947   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY,
07948                               H5P_DEFAULT);
07949   // Open the data set
07950   hid_t atomic_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, "/decay/atomic", H5P_DEFAULT);
07951   hid_t atomic_space = H5Dget_space(atomic_set);
07952   int atomic_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(atomic_space);
07953 
07954   // Read in the data
07955   atomic * atomic_array = new atomic[atomic_length];
07956   status = H5Dread(atomic_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT,
07957                    atomic_array);
07958 
07959   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
07960   status = H5Dclose(atomic_set);
07961   status = H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
07962 
07963   for (int i = 0; i < atomic_length; ++i) {
07964       atomic_data_map[atomic_array[i].z] = atomic_array[i];
07965   }
07966 
07967   delete[] atomic_array;
07968 
07969 }
07970 
07971 std::vector<std::pair<double, double> >
07972   pyne::calculate_xray_data(int z, double k_conv, double l_conv) {
07973   double xk = 0;
07974   double xka = 0;
07975   double xka1 = 0;
07976   double xka2 = 0;
07977   double xkb = 0;
07978   double xl = 0;
07979   if (!isnan(k_conv)) {
07980     xk = data_access<atomic> (z, offsetof(atomic, k_shell_fluor),
07981      atomic_data_map)*k_conv;
07982     xka = xk / (1.0 + data_access<atomic> (z, offsetof(atomic,
07983      kb_to_ka), atomic_data_map));
07984     xka1 = xka / (1.0 + data_access<atomic> (z, offsetof(atomic,
07985      ka2_to_ka1), atomic_data_map));
07986     xka2 = xka - xka1;
07987     xkb = xk - xka;
07988     if (!isnan(l_conv)) {
07989         xl = (l_conv + k_conv*data_access<atomic> (z, offsetof(atomic,
07990      prob), atomic_data_map))*data_access<atomic> (z, offsetof(atomic,
07991      l_shell_fluor), atomic_data_map);
07992     }
07993   } else if (!isnan(l_conv)) {
07994     xl = l_conv*data_access<atomic> (z, offsetof(atomic,
07995      l_shell_fluor), atomic_data_map);
07996   }
07997   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > result;
07998   result.push_back(std::make_pair(data_access<atomic> (z, offsetof(atomic,
07999      ka1_x_ray_en), atomic_data_map),xka1));
08000   result.push_back(std::make_pair(data_access<atomic> (z, offsetof(atomic,
08001      ka2_x_ray_en), atomic_data_map),xka2));
08002   result.push_back(std::make_pair(data_access<atomic> (z, offsetof(atomic,
08003      kb_x_ray_en), atomic_data_map),xkb));
08004   result.push_back(std::make_pair(data_access<atomic> (z, offsetof(atomic,
08005      l_x_ray_en), atomic_data_map),xl));
08006 
08007   return result;
08008 }
08009 
08010 
08011 //
08012 // Load level data
08013 //
08014 
08015 std::map<std::pair<int,double>, pyne::level_data> pyne::level_data_lvl_map;
08016 std::map<std::pair<int,unsigned int>,
08017   pyne::level_data> pyne::level_data_rx_map;
08018 
08019 
08020 template<> void pyne::_load_data<pyne::level_data>()
08021 {
08022 
08023   // Loads the level table into memory
08024   herr_t status;
08025 
08026   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
08027   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
08028     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
08029 
08030   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
08031   if (!ish5)
08032     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
08033 
08034   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
08035   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(level_data));
08036   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "nuc_id", HOFFSET(level_data, nuc_id),
08037                       H5T_NATIVE_INT);
08038   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "rx_id", HOFFSET(level_data, rx_id),
08039                      H5T_NATIVE_UINT);
08040   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "half_life", HOFFSET(level_data, half_life),
08041                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08042   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "level", HOFFSET(level_data, level),
08043                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08044   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "branch_ratio", HOFFSET(level_data, branch_ratio),
08045                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08046   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "metastable", HOFFSET(level_data, metastable),
08047                       H5T_NATIVE_INT);
08048   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "special", HOFFSET(level_data, special),
08049                       H5T_C_S1);
08050   // Open the HDF5 file
08051   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY,
08052                               H5P_DEFAULT);
08053   // Open the data set
08054   hid_t level_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, "/decay/level_list", H5P_DEFAULT);
08055   hid_t level_space = H5Dget_space(level_set);
08056   int level_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(level_space);
08057 
08058   // Read in the data
08059   level_data * level_array = new level_data[level_length];
08060   status = H5Dread(level_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT,
08061                    level_array);
08062 
08063   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
08064   status = H5Dclose(level_set);
08065   status = H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
08066 
08067   for (int i = 0; i < level_length; ++i) {
08068     if (level_array[i].rx_id == 0)
08069       level_data_lvl_map[std::make_pair(level_array[i].nuc_id,
08070                                         level_array[i].level)] = level_array[i];
08071     else
08072       level_data_rx_map[std::make_pair(level_array[i].nuc_id,
08073                                        level_array[i].rx_id)] = level_array[i];
08074   }
08075 
08076   delete[] level_array;
08077 }
08078 
08079 //
08080 // level id
08081 //
08082 int pyne::id_from_level(int nuc, double level, std::string special) {
08083   int nostate = (nuc / 10000) * 10000;
08084   if (level_data_lvl_map.empty()) {
08085     _load_data<level_data>();
08086   }
08087 
08088   std::map<std::pair<int, double>, level_data>::iterator nuc_lower, nuc_upper;
08089 
08090   nuc_lower = level_data_lvl_map.lower_bound(std::make_pair(nostate, 0.0));
08091   nuc_upper = level_data_lvl_map.upper_bound(std::make_pair(nostate+9999,
08092                                              DBL_MAX));
08093   double minv = DBL_MAX;
08094   //by default return input nuc_id with level stripped
08095   int ret_id = nuc;
08096   for (std::map<std::pair<int, double>, level_data>::iterator it=nuc_lower;
08097        it!=nuc_upper; ++it) {
08098     if ((abs(level - it->second.level) < minv) &&
08099     ((char)it->second.special == special.c_str()[0]) &&
08100     !isnan(it->second.level)) {
08101       minv = abs(level - it->second.level);
08102       ret_id = it->second.nuc_id;
08103     }
08104   }
08105   // This value was chosen so important transitions in U-235 are not missed
08106   if (minv > 3.0)
08107     return -nuc;
08108   else 
08109     return ret_id;
08110 }
08111 
08112 int pyne::id_from_level(int nuc, double level){
08113     return id_from_level(nuc, level, " ");
08114 }
08115 //
08116 // Metastable id data
08117 //
08118 
08119 int pyne::metastable_id(int nuc, int m) {
08120   int nostate = (nuc / 10000) * 10000;
08121   if (m==0) return nostate;
08122   if (level_data_lvl_map.empty()) {
08123     _load_data<level_data>();
08124   }
08125 
08126   std::map<std::pair<int, double>, level_data>::iterator nuc_lower, nuc_upper;
08127 
08128   nuc_lower = level_data_lvl_map.lower_bound(std::make_pair(nostate, 0.0));
08129   nuc_upper = level_data_lvl_map.upper_bound(std::make_pair(nostate+9999,
08130   DBL_MAX));
08131   for (std::map<std::pair<int, double>, level_data>::iterator it=nuc_lower;
08132   it!=nuc_upper; ++it) {
08133     if (it->second.metastable == m)
08134         return it->second.nuc_id;
08135   }
08136 
08137   return nuc;
08138 }
08139 
08140 int pyne::metastable_id(int nuc) {
08141   return metastable_id(nuc, 1);
08142 }
08143 
08144 //
08145 // Decay children data
08146 //
08147 
08148 
08149 std::set<int> pyne::decay_children(int nuc) {
08150   // make sure spontaneous fission data is loaded
08151   if (wimsdfpy_data.empty())
08152     _load_wimsdfpy();
08153 
08154   std::vector<unsigned int> part = data_access<unsigned int, level_data>(nuc,
08155     offsetof(level_data, rx_id), level_data_rx_map);
08156   std::vector<unsigned int>::iterator it = part.begin();
08157   std::set<int> result;
08158   for (; it != part.end(); ++it) {
08159     switch (*it) {
08160       case 36125: {
08161         // internal conversion, rx == 'it'
08162         result.insert((nuc /10000) * 10000);
08163         break;
08164       }
08165       case 36565: {
08166         // spontaneous fission, rx == 'sf'
08167         std::map<std::pair<int, int>, double>::iterator sf = wimsdfpy_data.begin();
08168         for (; sf != wimsdfpy_data.end(); ++sf)
08169           if (sf->first.first == nuc)
08170             result.insert(sf->first.second);
08171         break;
08172       }
08173       default: {
08174         result.insert((rxname::child(nuc, *it, "decay") /10000) * 10000);
08175       }
08176     }
08177   }
08178   return result;
08179 }
08180 
08181 std::set<int> pyne::decay_children(char * nuc)
08182 {
08183   return decay_children(nucname::id(nuc));
08184 };
08185 
08186 std::set<int> pyne::decay_children(std::string nuc)
08187 {
08188   return decay_children(nucname::id(nuc));
08189 };

08195 double pyne::state_energy(int nuc)
08196 {
08197   std::vector<double> result = data_access<double, level_data>(nuc, 0.0,
08198   DBL_MAX, offsetof(level_data, level), level_data_lvl_map);
08199   if (result.size() == 1)
08200     return result[0]/1000.0;
08201   return 0.0;
08202 }

08216 //
08217 // Decay constant data
08218 //
08219 
08220 double pyne::decay_const(int nuc)
08221 {
08222     std::vector<double> result = data_access<double, level_data>(nuc, 0.0,
08223       DBL_MAX, offsetof(level_data, half_life), level_data_lvl_map);
08224     if (result.size() == 1) {
08225         return log(2.0)/result[0];
08226     }
08227     return 0.0;
08228 }

08244 // Half-life data
08245 //

08247     std::vector<double> result = data_access<double, level_data>(nuc, 0.0,
08248     DBL_MAX, offsetof(level_data, half_life), level_data_lvl_map);
08249     if (result.size() == 1) {
08250         return result[0];
08251     }
08252     return 1.0/0.0;
08253 };

08266 
08267 //
08268 // Branch ratio data
08269 //
08270 double pyne::branch_ratio(std::pair<int, int> from_to) {
08271   using std::vector;
08272   using pyne::nucname::groundstate;
08273   // make sure spontaneous fission data is loaded
08274   if (wimsdfpy_data.empty())
08275     _load_wimsdfpy();
08276 
08277   vector<unsigned int> part1 = \
08278     data_access<unsigned int, level_data>(from_to.first, offsetof(level_data, rx_id),
08279                                           level_data_rx_map);
08280   vector<double> part2 = \
08281     data_access<double, level_data>(from_to.first, offsetof(level_data, branch_ratio),
08282                                     level_data_rx_map);
08283   double result = 0.0;
08284   if ((from_to.first == from_to.second) && (decay_const(from_to.first) == 0.0))
08285     return 1.0;
08286   for (vector<unsigned int>::size_type i = 0; i < part1.size(); ++i) {
08287     if ((part1[i] == 36125) &&
08288         (groundstate(from_to.first) == groundstate(from_to.second)) &&
08289         (from_to.second % 10000 == 0)) {
08290       // internal conversion, rx == 'it'
08291       result = 1.0;
08292       break;
08293     } else if (part1[i] == 36565) {
08294       // spontaneous fission, rx == 'sf'
08295       result += part2[i] * 0.01 * wimsdfpy_data[from_to];
08296     } else if ((part1[i] != 0) && (groundstate(rxname::child(from_to.first,
08297                                    part1[i], "decay")) == from_to.second)) {
08298       result += part2[i] * 0.01;
08299     }
08300   }
08301   return result;
08302 }
08303 
08304 double pyne::branch_ratio(int from_nuc, int to_nuc) {
08305   return branch_ratio(std::pair<int, int>(nucname::id(from_nuc),
08306                                           nucname::id(to_nuc)));
08307 };
08308 
08309 double pyne::branch_ratio(char * from_nuc, char * to_nuc) {
08310   return branch_ratio(std::pair<int, int>(nucname::id(from_nuc),
08311                                           nucname::id(to_nuc)));
08312 };
08313 
08314 double pyne::branch_ratio(std::string from_nuc, std::string to_nuc) {
08315   return branch_ratio(std::pair<int, int>(nucname::id(from_nuc),
08316                                           nucname::id(to_nuc)));
08317 };

08319 std::map<std::pair<int, int>, pyne::decay> pyne::decay_data = \
08320   std::map<std::pair<int, int>, pyne::decay>();
08321 
08322 template<> void pyne::_load_data<pyne::decay>() {
08323 
08324   // Loads the decay table into memory
08325   herr_t status;
08326 
08327   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
08328   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
08329     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
08330 
08331   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
08332   if (!ish5)
08333     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
08334 
08335   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
08336   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(decay));
08337   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "parent", HOFFSET(decay, parent),
08338                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
08339   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "child", HOFFSET(decay, child),
08340                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
08341   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "decay", HOFFSET(decay, decay),
08342                      H5T_NATIVE_UINT);
08343   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "half_life", HOFFSET(decay, half_life),
08344                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08345   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "half_life_error", HOFFSET(decay,
08346                      half_life_error), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08347   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "branch_ratio", HOFFSET(decay, branch_ratio),
08348                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08349   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "branch_ratio_error", HOFFSET(decay, branch_ratio_error),
08350                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08351   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "photon_branch_ratio", HOFFSET(decay,
08352                      photon_branch_ratio), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08353   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "photon_branch_ratio_err", HOFFSET(decay,
08354                      photon_branch_ratio_error), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08355   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "beta_branch_ratio", HOFFSET(decay,
08356                      beta_branch_ratio), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08357   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "beta_branch_ratio_err", HOFFSET(decay,
08358                      beta_branch_ratio_error), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08359 
08360   // Open the HDF5 file
08361   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY,
08362                               H5P_DEFAULT);
08363 
08364   // Open the data set
08365   hid_t decay_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, "/decay/decays", H5P_DEFAULT);
08366   hid_t decay_space = H5Dget_space(decay_set);
08367   int decay_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(decay_space);
08368 
08369   // Read in the data
08370   decay * decay_array = new decay[decay_length];
08371   status = H5Dread(decay_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT,
08372                    decay_array);
08373 
08374   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
08375   status = H5Dclose(decay_set);
08376   status = H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
08377 
08378   for (int i = 0; i < decay_length; ++i) {
08379     decay_data[std::make_pair(decay_array[i].parent, decay_array[i].child)] = \
08380       decay_array[i];
08381   }
08382   delete[] decay_array;
08383 }

08462 
08463 std::map<std::pair<int, double>, pyne::gamma> pyne::gamma_data;
08464 
08465 template<> void pyne::_load_data<pyne::gamma>() {
08466 
08467   // Loads the gamma table into memory
08468   herr_t status;
08469 
08470   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
08471   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
08472     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
08473 
08474   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
08475   if (!ish5)
08476     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
08477 
08478   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
08479   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(gamma));
08480   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "from_nuc", HOFFSET(gamma, from_nuc),
08481                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
08482   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "to_nuc", HOFFSET(gamma, to_nuc),
08483                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
08484   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "parent_nuc", HOFFSET(gamma, parent_nuc),
08485                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
08486   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "child_nuc", HOFFSET(gamma, child_nuc),
08487                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
08488   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "energy", HOFFSET(gamma, energy),
08489                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08490   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "energy_err", HOFFSET(gamma, energy_err),
08491                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08492   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "photon_intensity", HOFFSET(gamma,
08493                      photon_intensity), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08494   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "photon_intensity_err", HOFFSET(gamma,
08495                      photon_intensity_err), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08496   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "conv_intensity", HOFFSET(gamma,
08497                      conv_intensity), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08498   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "conv_intensity_err", HOFFSET(gamma,
08499                      conv_intensity_err), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08500   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "total_intensity", HOFFSET(gamma,
08501                      total_intensity), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08502   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "total_intensity_err", HOFFSET(gamma,
08503                      total_intensity_err), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08504   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "k_conv_e", HOFFSET(gamma, k_conv_e),
08505                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08506   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "l_conv_e", HOFFSET(gamma, l_conv_e),
08507                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08508   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "m_conv_e", HOFFSET(gamma, m_conv_e),
08509                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08510 
08511 
08512   // Open the HDF5 file
08513   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY,
08514                               H5P_DEFAULT);
08515 
08516   // Open the data set
08517   hid_t gamma_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, "/decay/gammas", H5P_DEFAULT);
08518   hid_t gamma_space = H5Dget_space(gamma_set);
08519   int gamma_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(gamma_space);
08520 
08521   // Read in the data
08522   gamma * gamma_array = new gamma[gamma_length];
08523   status = H5Dread(gamma_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT,
08524                    gamma_array);
08525 
08526   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
08527   status = H5Dclose(gamma_set);
08528   status = H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
08529 
08530   for (int i = 0; i < gamma_length; ++i) {
08531     if ((gamma_array[i].parent_nuc != 0) && !isnan(gamma_array[i].energy))
08532       gamma_data[std::make_pair(gamma_array[i].parent_nuc,
08533         gamma_array[i].energy)] = gamma_array[i];
08534   }
08535   delete[] gamma_array;
08536 }

08668 
08669 std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > pyne::gamma_xrays(int parent) {
08670   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > result;
08671   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > temp;
08672   std::vector<double> k_list = data_access<double, gamma>(parent, 0.0, DBL_MAX,
08673     offsetof(gamma, k_conv_e), gamma_data);
08674   std::vector<double> l_list = data_access<double, gamma>(parent, 0.0, DBL_MAX,
08675     offsetof(gamma, l_conv_e), gamma_data);
08676   std::vector<int> children = data_access<int, gamma>(parent, 0.0,
08677     DBL_MAX, offsetof(gamma, from_nuc), gamma_data);
08678   std::vector<int> decay_children = decay_data_children(parent);
08679   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > decay_br =
08680     decay_photon_branch_ratios(parent);
08681   for(int i = 0; i < k_list.size(); ++i){
08682     for (int j = 0; j < decay_children.size(); ++j) {
08683       if (nucname::zzzaaa(children[i]) == nucname::zzzaaa(decay_children[j])) {
08684         temp = calculate_xray_data(nucname::znum(children[i]),
08685           k_list[i]*decay_br[j].first, l_list[i]*decay_br[j].first);
08686         for (int k = 0; k < temp.size(); ++k) {
08687           if (!isnan(temp[k].second) && !isnan(temp[k].first)) {
08688             int found = 0;
08689             for (int l = 0; l < result.size(); ++l) {
08690               if (temp[k].first == result[l].first) {
08691                 result[l].second = result[l].second + temp[k].second;
08692                 found = 1;
08693                 break;
08694               }
08695             }
08696             if (found == 0) {
08697               result.push_back(temp[k]);
08698             }
08699           }
08700         }
08701         break;
08702       }
08703     }
08704   }
08705   return result;
08706 };
08707 
08708 std::map<std::pair<int, double>, pyne::alpha> pyne::alpha_data;
08709 
08710 template<> void pyne::_load_data<pyne::alpha>() {
08711 
08712   // Loads the alpha table into memory
08713   herr_t status;
08714 
08715   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
08716   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
08717     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
08718 
08719   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
08720   if (!ish5)
08721     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
08722 
08723   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
08724   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(alpha));
08725   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "from_nuc", HOFFSET(alpha, from_nuc),
08726                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
08727   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "to_nuc", HOFFSET(alpha, to_nuc),
08728                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
08729   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "energy", HOFFSET(alpha, energy),
08730                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08731   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "intensity", HOFFSET(alpha, intensity),
08732                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08733 
08734 
08735   // Open the HDF5 file
08736   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY,
08737                               H5P_DEFAULT);
08738 
08739   // Open the data set
08740   hid_t alpha_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, "/decay/alphas", H5P_DEFAULT);
08741   hid_t alpha_space = H5Dget_space(alpha_set);
08742   int alpha_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(alpha_space);
08743 
08744   // Read in the data
08745   alpha * alpha_array = new alpha[alpha_length];
08746   status = H5Dread(alpha_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT,
08747                    alpha_array);
08748 
08749   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
08750   status = H5Dclose(alpha_set);
08751   status = H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
08752 
08753   for (int i = 0; i < alpha_length; ++i) {
08754     if ((alpha_array[i].from_nuc != 0) && !isnan(alpha_array[i].energy))
08755       alpha_data[std::make_pair(alpha_array[i].from_nuc, alpha_array[i].energy)]
08756         = alpha_array[i];
08757   }
08758   delete[] alpha_array;
08759 }
08760

08762   return data_access<double, alpha>(parent, 0.0, DBL_MAX,
08763                      offsetof(alpha,energy), alpha_data);
08764 };

08872 template<> void pyne::_load_data<pyne::ecbp>() {
08873 
08874   // Loads the ecbp table into memory
08875   herr_t status;
08876 
08877   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
08878   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
08879     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
08880 
08881   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
08882   if (!ish5)
08883     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
08884 
08885   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
08886   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(ecbp));
08887   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "from_nuc", HOFFSET(ecbp, from_nuc),
08888                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
08889   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "to_nuc", HOFFSET(ecbp, to_nuc),
08890                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
08891   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "endpoint_energy", HOFFSET(ecbp,
08892                      endpoint_energy),H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08893   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "avg_energy", HOFFSET(ecbp, avg_energy),
08894                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08895   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "beta_plus_intensity", HOFFSET(ecbp,
08896                      beta_plus_intensity), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08897   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ec_intensity", HOFFSET(ecbp, ec_intensity),
08898                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08899   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "k_conv_e", HOFFSET(ecbp, k_conv_e),
08900                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08901   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "l_conv_e", HOFFSET(ecbp, l_conv_e),
08902                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08903   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "m_conv_e", HOFFSET(ecbp, m_conv_e),
08904                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08905 
08906   // Open the HDF5 file
08907   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY,
08908                               H5P_DEFAULT);
08909 
08910   // Open the data set
08911   hid_t ecbp_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, "/decay/ecbp", H5P_DEFAULT);
08912   hid_t ecbp_space = H5Dget_space(ecbp_set);
08913   int ecbp_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(ecbp_space);
08914 
08915   // Read in the data
08916   ecbp * ecbp_array = new ecbp[ecbp_length];
08917   status = H5Dread(ecbp_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT, ecbp_array);
08918 
08919   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
08920   status = H5Dclose(ecbp_set);
08921   status = H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
08922 
08923   for (int i = 0; i < ecbp_length; ++i) {
08924     if ((ecbp_array[i].from_nuc != 0) && !isnan(ecbp_array[i].avg_energy))
08925       ecbp_data[std::make_pair(ecbp_array[i].from_nuc, ecbp_array[i].avg_energy)]
08926         = ecbp_array[i];
08927   }
08928   delete[] ecbp_array;
08929 }

08965 
08966 std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > pyne::ecbp_xrays(int parent) {
08967   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > result;
08968   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > temp;
08969   std::vector<double> k_list = data_access<double, ecbp>(parent, 0.0, DBL_MAX,
08970     offsetof(ecbp, k_conv_e), ecbp_data);
08971   std::vector<double> l_list = data_access<double, ecbp>(parent, 0.0, DBL_MAX,
08972     offsetof(ecbp, l_conv_e), ecbp_data);
08973   std::vector<int> children = data_access<int, ecbp>(parent, 0.0, DBL_MAX,
08974     offsetof(ecbp, to_nuc), ecbp_data);
08975   std::vector<int> decay_children = decay_data_children(parent);
08976   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > decay_br =
08977     decay_beta_branch_ratios(parent);
08978   for(int i = 0; i < k_list.size(); ++i){
08979     for (int j = 0; j < decay_children.size(); ++j) {
08980       if (nucname::zzzaaa(children[i]) == nucname::zzzaaa(decay_children[j])) {
08981         temp = calculate_xray_data(nucname::znum(children[i]),
08982           k_list[i]*decay_br[j].first, l_list[i]*decay_br[j].first);
08983         for (int k = 0; k < temp.size(); ++k) {
08984           if (!isnan(temp[k].second) && !isnan(temp[k].first)) {
08985             int found = 0;
08986             for (int l = 0; l < result.size(); ++l) {
08987               if (temp[k].first == result[l].first) {
08988                 result[l].second = result[l].second + temp[k].second;
08989                 found = 1;
08990                 break;
08991               }
08992             }
08993             if (found == 0) {
08994               result.push_back(temp[k]);
08995             }
08996           }
08997         }
08998         break;
08999       }
09000     }
09001   }
09002   return result;
09003 };

09007 ///////////////////////////
09008 
09009 std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > pyne::gammas(int parent_state_id) {
09010   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > result;
09011   double decay_c = decay_const(parent_state_id);
09012   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > energies = gamma_energy(parent_state_id);
09013   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > intensities =
09014     gamma_photon_intensity(parent_state_id);
09015   std::vector<std::pair<int, int> > children = gamma_from_to(parent_state_id);
09016   std::vector<int> decay_children = decay_data_children(parent_state_id);
09017   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > decay_br =
09018     decay_photon_branch_ratios(parent_state_id);
09019   for (int i = 0; i < children.size(); ++i) {
09020     for (int j = 0; j < decay_children.size(); ++j) {
09021       if (nucname::zzzaaa(children[i].first) == nucname::zzzaaa(decay_children[j])) {
09022         result.push_back(std::make_pair(energies[i].first,
09023           decay_c*intensities[i].first*decay_br[j].first));
09024       }
09025     }
09026   }
09027   return result;
09028 }
09029 
09030 std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > pyne::alphas(int parent_state_id) {
09031   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > result;
09032   double decay_c = decay_const(parent_state_id);
09033   std::vector<double> energies = alpha_energy(parent_state_id);
09034   std::vector<double> intensities = alpha_intensity(parent_state_id);
09035   std::vector<int> children = alpha_child(parent_state_id);
09036   std::vector<int> decay_children = decay_data_children(parent_state_id);
09037   std::vector<double> decay_br = decay_branch_ratios(parent_state_id);
09038   for (int i = 0; i < children.size(); ++i) {
09039     for (int j = 0; j < decay_children.size(); ++j) {
09040       if (nucname::zzzaaa(children[i]) == nucname::zzzaaa(decay_children[j])) {
09041         result.push_back(std::make_pair(energies[i],
09042           decay_c*decay_br[j]*intensities[i]));
09043       }
09044     }
09045   }
09046   return result;
09047 }
09048 
09049 std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > pyne::betas(int parent_state_id) {
09050   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > result;
09051   double decay_c = decay_const(parent_state_id);
09052   std::vector<double> energies = beta_average_energy(parent_state_id);
09053   std::vector<double> intensities = beta_intensity(parent_state_id);
09054   std::vector<int> children = beta_child(parent_state_id);
09055   std::vector<int> decay_children = decay_data_children(parent_state_id);
09056   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > decay_br =
09057     decay_beta_branch_ratios(parent_state_id);
09058   for (int i = 0; i < children.size(); ++i) {
09059     for (int j = 0; j < decay_children.size(); ++j) {
09060       if (nucname::zzzaaa(children[i]) == nucname::zzzaaa(decay_children[j])) {
09061         result.push_back(std::make_pair(energies[i],
09062           decay_c*decay_br[j].first*intensities[i]));
09063         break;
09064       }
09065     }
09066   }
09067   return result;
09068 }
09069 
09070 std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > pyne::xrays(int parent) {
09071   double decay_c = decay_const(parent);
09072   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > result;
09073   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > temp;
09074   std::vector<double> k_list = data_access<double, ecbp>(parent, 0.0, DBL_MAX,
09075     offsetof(ecbp, k_conv_e), ecbp_data);
09076   std::vector<double> l_list = data_access<double, ecbp>(parent, 0.0, DBL_MAX,
09077     offsetof(ecbp, l_conv_e), ecbp_data);
09078   std::vector<int> children = data_access<int, ecbp>(parent, 0.0, DBL_MAX,
09079                      offsetof(ecbp, to_nuc), ecbp_data);
09080   std::vector<int> decay_children = decay_data_children(parent);
09081   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > decay_br =
09082     decay_beta_branch_ratios(parent);
09083   for(int i = 0; i < k_list.size(); ++i){
09084     for (int j = 0; j < decay_children.size(); ++j) {
09085       if (nucname::zzzaaa(children[i]) == nucname::zzzaaa(decay_children[j])) {
09086         temp = calculate_xray_data(nucname::znum(children[i]),
09087           k_list[i]*decay_br[j].first, l_list[i]*decay_br[j].first);
09088         for (int k = 0; k < temp.size(); ++k) {
09089           if (!isnan(temp[k].second) && !isnan(temp[k].first)) {
09090             int found = 0;
09091             for (int l = 0; l < result.size(); ++l) {
09092               if (temp[k].first == result[l].first) {
09093                 result[l].second = result[l].second + temp[k].second;
09094                 found = 1;
09095                 break;
09096               }
09097             }
09098             if (found == 0) {
09099               result.push_back(temp[k]);
09100             }
09101           }
09102         }
09103         break;
09104       }
09105     }
09106   }
09107   std::vector<double> gk_list = data_access<double, gamma>(parent, 0.0, DBL_MAX,
09108     offsetof(gamma, k_conv_e), gamma_data);
09109   std::vector<double> gl_list = data_access<double, gamma>(parent, 0.0, DBL_MAX,
09110     offsetof(gamma, l_conv_e), gamma_data);
09111   std::vector<int> gchildren = data_access<int, gamma>(parent, 0.0,
09112     DBL_MAX, offsetof(gamma, from_nuc), gamma_data);
09113   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > decay_nrbr =
09114     decay_photon_branch_ratios(parent);
09115   for(int i = 0; i < gk_list.size(); ++i){
09116     for (int j = 0; j < decay_children.size(); ++j) {
09117       if (nucname::zzzaaa(gchildren[i]) == nucname::zzzaaa(decay_children[j])) {
09118         temp = calculate_xray_data(nucname::znum(gchildren[i]),
09119           gk_list[i]*decay_nrbr[j].first, gl_list[i]*decay_nrbr[j].first);
09120         for (int k = 0; k < temp.size(); ++k) {
09121           if (!isnan(temp[k].second) && !isnan(temp[k].first)) {
09122             int found = 0;
09123             for (int l = 0; l < result.size(); ++l) {
09124               if (temp[k].first == result[l].first) {
09125                 result[l].second = result[l].second + temp[k].second;
09126                 found = 1;
09127                 break;
09128               }
09129             }
09130             if (found == 0) {
09131               result.push_back(temp[k]);
09132             }
09133           }
09134         }
09135         break;
09136       }
09137     }
09138   }
09139 
09140   for(int i = 0; i < result.size(); ++i)
09141     result[i].second = result[i].second * decay_c;
09142   return result;
09143 };

09149 typedef struct simple_xs {
09150   int nuc;
09151   double sigma_t;
09152   double sigma_s;
09153   double sigma_e;
09154   double sigma_i;
09155   double sigma_a;
09156   double sigma_gamma;
09157   double sigma_f;
09158   double sigma_alpha;
09159   double sigma_proton;
09160   double sigma_deut;
09161   double sigma_trit;
09162   double sigma_2n;
09163   double sigma_3n;
09164   double sigma_4n;
09165 } simple_xs;
09166 
09167 std::map<std::string, std::map<int, std::map<int, double> > > pyne::simple_xs_map;
09168 
09169 // loads the simple cross section data for the specified energy band from
09170 // the nuc_data.h5 file into memory.
09171 static void _load_simple_xs_map(std::string energy) {
09172   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
09173   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
09174     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
09175 
09176   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
09177   if (!ish5)
09178     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
09179 
09180   using pyne::rxname::id;
09181   std::map<unsigned int, size_t> rxns;
09182   rxns[id("tot")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_t);
09183   rxns[id("scat")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_s);
09184   rxns[id("elas")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_e);
09185   rxns[id("inel")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_i);
09186   rxns[id("abs")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_a);
09187   rxns[id("gamma")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_gamma);
09188   rxns[id("fiss")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_f);
09189   rxns[id("alpha")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_alpha);
09190   rxns[id("proton")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_proton);
09191   rxns[id("deut")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_deut);
09192   rxns[id("trit")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_trit);
09193   rxns[id("z_2n")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_2n);
09194   rxns[id("z_3n")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_3n);
09195   rxns[id("z_4n")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_4n);
09196 
09197   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
09198   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(simple_xs));
09199   H5Tinsert(desc, "nuc",   HOFFSET(simple_xs, nuc),   H5T_NATIVE_INT);
09200   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_t",  HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_t),  H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09201   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_s", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_s), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09202   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_e", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_e), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09203   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_i", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_i), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09204   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_a", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_a), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09205   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_gamma", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_gamma), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09206   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_f", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_f), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09207   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_alpha", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_alpha), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09208   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_proton", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_proton), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09209   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_deut", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_deut), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09210   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_trit", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_trit), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09211   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_2n", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_2n), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09212   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_3n", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_3n), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09213   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_4n", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_4n), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09214 
09215   // Open the HDF5 file
09216   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY, H5P_DEFAULT);
09217 
09218   // build path to prober simple xs table
09219   std::string path = "/neutron/simple_xs/" + energy;
09220 
09221   // Open the data set
09222   hid_t simple_xs_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, path.c_str(), H5P_DEFAULT);
09223   hid_t simple_xs_space = H5Dget_space(simple_xs_set);
09224   int n = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(simple_xs_space);
09225 
09226   // Read in the data
09227   simple_xs* array = new simple_xs[n];
09228   H5Dread(simple_xs_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT, array);
09229 
09230   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
09231   H5Dclose(simple_xs_set);
09232   H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
09233 
09234   // Ok now that we have the array of stucts, put it in the map
09235   for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
09236     std::map<unsigned int, size_t>::iterator it;
09237     for (it = rxns.begin(); it != rxns.end(); ++it) {
09238       double xs = *(double*)((char*)&array[i] + it->second);
09239       pyne::simple_xs_map[energy][array[i].nuc][it->first] = xs;
09240     }
09241   }
09242   delete[] array;
09243 }
09244 
09245 double pyne::simple_xs(int nuc, int rx_id, std::string energy) {
09246   std::set<std::string> energies;
09247   energies.insert("thermal");
09248   energies.insert("thermal_maxwell_ave");
09249   energies.insert("resonance_integral");
09250   energies.insert("fourteen_MeV");
09251   energies.insert("fission_spectrum_ave");
09252 
09253   if (energies.count(energy) == 0) {
09254     throw InvalidSimpleXS("Energy '" + energy +
09255         "' is not a valid simple_xs group");
09256   } else if (simple_xs_map.count(energy) == 0) {
09257     _load_simple_xs_map(energy);
09258   }
09259 
09260   if (simple_xs_map[energy].count(nuc) == 0) {
09261     throw InvalidSimpleXS(rxname::name(rx_id) +
09262         " is not a valid simple_xs nuclide");
09263   } else if (simple_xs_map[energy][nuc].count(rx_id) == 0) {
09264     throw InvalidSimpleXS(rxname::name(rx_id) +
09265         " is not a valid simple_xs reaction");
09266   }
09267 
09268   return simple_xs_map[energy][nuc][rx_id];
09269 }
09270 
09271 double pyne::simple_xs(int nuc, std::string rx, std::string energy) {
09272   return pyne::simple_xs(nucname::id(nuc), rxname::id(rx), energy);
09273 }
09274 double pyne::simple_xs(std::string nuc, int rx, std::string energy) {
09275   return pyne::simple_xs(nucname::id(nuc), rxname::id(rx), energy);
09276 }
09277 double pyne::simple_xs(std::string nuc, std::string rx, std::string energy) {
09278   return pyne::simple_xs(nucname::id(nuc), rxname::id(rx), energy);
09279 }

09383 /* This header provides common string manipulation support, such as UTF-8,
09384  * portable conversion from/to string...
09385  *
09386  * It is an internal header that must not be exposed.
09387  */
09388 
09389 namespace Json {
09390 
09391 /// Converts a unicode code-point to UTF-8.
09392 static inline std::string 
09393 codePointToUTF8(unsigned int cp) {
09394    std::string result;
09395    
09396    // based on description from http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UTF-8
09397 
09398    if (cp <= 0x7f) {
09399       result.resize(1);
09400       result[0] = static_cast<char>(cp);
09401    } else if (cp <= 0x7FF) {
09402       result.resize(2);
09403       result[1] = static_cast<char>(0x80 | (0x3f & cp));
09404       result[0] = static_cast<char>(0xC0 | (0x1f & (cp >> 6)));
09405    } else if (cp <= 0xFFFF) {
09406       result.resize(3);
09407       result[2] = static_cast<char>(0x80 | (0x3f & cp));
09408       result[1] = 0x80 | static_cast<char>((0x3f & (cp >> 6)));
09409       result[0] = 0xE0 | static_cast<char>((0xf & (cp >> 12)));
09410    } else if (cp <= 0x10FFFF) {
09411       result.resize(4);
09412       result[3] = static_cast<char>(0x80 | (0x3f & cp));
09413       result[2] = static_cast<char>(0x80 | (0x3f & (cp >> 6)));
09414       result[1] = static_cast<char>(0x80 | (0x3f & (cp >> 12)));
09415       result[0] = static_cast<char>(0xF0 | (0x7 & (cp >> 18)));
09416    }
09417 
09418    return result;
09419 }
09420 
09421 
09422 /// Returns true if ch is a control character (in range [0,32[).
09423 static inline bool 
09424 isControlCharacter(char ch) {
09425    return ch > 0 && ch <= 0x1F;
09426 }
09427 
09428 
09429 enum { 
09430    /// Constant that specify the size of the buffer that must be passed to uintToString.
09431    uintToStringBufferSize = 3*sizeof(LargestUInt)+1 
09432 };
09433 
09434 // Defines a char buffer for use with uintToString().
09435 typedef char UIntToStringBuffer[uintToStringBufferSize];
09436 
09437 
09438 /** Converts an unsigned integer to string.
09439  * @param value Unsigned interger to convert to string
09440  * @param current Input/Output string buffer. 
09441  *        Must have at least uintToStringBufferSize chars free.
09442  */
09443 static inline void 
09444 uintToString( LargestUInt value, 
09445               char *&current ) {
09446    *--current = 0;
09447    do {
09448       *--current = char(value % 10) + '0';
09449       value /= 10;
09450    }
09451    while ( value != 0 );
09452 }

09534                  Reader::Location end ) {
09535    for ( ;begin < end; ++begin )
09536       if ( *begin == '\n'  ||  *begin == '\r' )
09537          return true;
09538    return false;

09554 
09555 bool
09556 Reader::parse( const std::string &document, 
09557                Value &root,
09558                bool collectComments ) {
09559    document_ = document;
09560    const char *begin = document_.c_str();
09561    const char *end = begin + document_.length();
09562    return parse( begin, end, root, collectComments );
09563 }
09564 
09565 
09566 bool
09567 Reader::parse( std::istream& sin,
09568                Value &root,
09569                bool collectComments ) {
09570    //std::istream_iterator<char> begin(sin);
09571    //std::istream_iterator<char> end;
09572    // Those would allow streamed input from a file, if parse() were a
09573    // template function.
09574 
09575    // Since std::string is reference-counted, this at least does not
09576    // create an extra copy.
09577    std::string doc;
09578    std::getline(sin, doc, (char)EOF);
09579    return parse( doc, root, collectComments );
09580 }
09581 
09582 bool 
09583 Reader::parse( const char *beginDoc, const char *endDoc, 
09584                Value &root,
09585                bool collectComments ) {
09586    if ( !features_.allowComments_ ) {
09587       collectComments = false;
09588    }
09589 
09590    begin_ = beginDoc;
09591    end_ = endDoc;
09592    collectComments_ = collectComments;
09593    current_ = begin_;
09594    lastValueEnd_ = 0;
09595    lastValue_ = 0;
09596    commentsBefore_ = "";
09597    errors_.clear();
09598    while ( !nodes_.empty() )
09599       nodes_.pop();
09600    nodes_.push( &root );
09601    
09602    bool successful = readValue();
09603    Token token;
09604    skipCommentTokens( token );
09605    if ( collectComments_  &&  !commentsBefore_.empty() )
09606       root.setComment( commentsBefore_, commentAfter );
09607    if ( features_.strictRoot_ ) {
09608       if ( !root.isArray()  &&  !root.isObject() ) {
09609          // Set error location to start of doc, ideally should be first token found in doc
09610          token.type_ = tokenError;
09611          token.start_ = beginDoc;
09612          token.end_ = endDoc;
09613          addError( "A valid JSON document must be either an array or an object value.",
09614                    token );
09615          return false;
09616       }
09617    }
09618    return successful;
09619 }
09620 
09621 
09622 bool
09623 Reader::readValue() {
09624    Token token;
09625    skipCommentTokens( token );
09626    bool successful = true;
09627 
09628    if ( collectComments_  &&  !commentsBefore_.empty() ) {
09629       currentValue().setComment( commentsBefore_, commentBefore );
09630       commentsBefore_ = "";
09631    }
09632 
09633 
09634    switch ( token.type_ ) {
09635    case tokenObjectBegin:
09636       successful = readObject( token );
09637       break;
09638    case tokenArrayBegin:
09639       successful = readArray( token );
09640       break;
09641    case tokenNumber:
09642       successful = decodeNumber( token );
09643       break;
09644    case tokenString:
09645       successful = decodeString( token );
09646       break;
09647    case tokenTrue:
09648       currentValue() = true;
09649       break;
09650    case tokenFalse:
09651       currentValue() = false;
09652       break;
09653    case tokenNull:
09654       currentValue() = Value();
09655       break;
09656    default:
09657       return addError( "Syntax error: value, object or array expected.", token );
09658    }
09659 
09660    if ( collectComments_ ) {
09661       lastValueEnd_ = current_;
09662       lastValue_ = &currentValue();
09663    }
09664 
09665    return successful;
09666 }
09667 
09668 
09669 void 
09670 Reader::skipCommentTokens( Token &token ) {
09671    if ( features_.allowComments_ ) {
09672       do {
09673          readToken( token );
09674       }
09675       while ( token.type_ == tokenComment );
09676    } else {
09677       readToken( token );
09678    }
09679 }
09680 
09681 
09682 bool 
09683 Reader::expectToken( TokenType type, Token &token, const char *message ) {
09684    readToken( token );
09685    if ( token.type_ != type )
09686       return addError( message, token );
09687    return true;
09688 }
09689 
09690 
09691 bool 
09692 Reader::readToken( Token &token ) {
09693    skipSpaces();
09694    token.start_ = current_;
09695    Char c = getNextChar();
09696    bool ok = true;
09697    switch ( c ) {
09698    case '{':
09699       token.type_ = tokenObjectBegin;
09700       break;
09701    case '}':
09702       token.type_ = tokenObjectEnd;
09703       break;
09704    case '[':
09705       token.type_ = tokenArrayBegin;
09706       break;
09707    case ']':
09708       token.type_ = tokenArrayEnd;
09709       break;
09710    case '"':
09711       token.type_ = tokenString;
09712       ok = readString();
09713       break;
09714    case '/':
09715       token.type_ = tokenComment;
09716       ok = readComment();
09717       break;
09718    case '0':
09719    case '1':
09720    case '2':
09721    case '3':
09722    case '4':
09723    case '5':
09724    case '6':
09725    case '7':
09726    case '8':
09727    case '9':
09728    case '-':
09729       token.type_ = tokenNumber;
09730       readNumber();
09731       break;
09732    case 't':
09733       token.type_ = tokenTrue;
09734       ok = match( "rue", 3 );
09735       break;
09736    case 'f':
09737       token.type_ = tokenFalse;
09738       ok = match( "alse", 4 );
09739       break;
09740    case 'n':
09741       token.type_ = tokenNull;
09742       ok = match( "ull", 3 );
09743       break;
09744    case ',':
09745       token.type_ = tokenArraySeparator;
09746       break;
09747    case ':':
09748       token.type_ = tokenMemberSeparator;
09749       break;
09750    case 0:
09751       token.type_ = tokenEndOfStream;
09752       break;
09753    default:
09754       ok = false;
09755       break;
09756    }
09757    if ( !ok )
09758       token.type_ = tokenError;
09759    token.end_ = current_;
09760    return true;
09761 }
09762 
09763 
09764 void 
09765 Reader::skipSpaces() {
09766    while ( current_ != end_ ) {
09767       Char c = *current_;
09768       if ( c == ' '  ||  c == '\t'  ||  c == '\r'  ||  c == '\n' )
09769          ++current_;
09770       else
09771          break;
09772    }
09773 }
09774 
09775 
09776 bool 
09777 Reader::match( Location pattern, 
09778                int patternLength ) {
09779    if ( end_ - current_ < patternLength )
09780       return false;
09781    int index = patternLength;
09782    while ( index-- )
09783       if ( current_[index] != pattern[index] )
09784          return false;
09785    current_ += patternLength;
09786    return true;
09787 }
09788 
09789 
09790 bool
09791 Reader::readComment() {
09792    Location commentBegin = current_ - 1;
09793    Char c = getNextChar();
09794    bool successful = false;
09795    if ( c == '*' )
09796       successful = readCStyleComment();
09797    else if ( c == '/' )
09798       successful = readCppStyleComment();
09799    if ( !successful )
09800       return false;
09801 
09802    if ( collectComments_ ) {
09803       CommentPlacement placement = commentBefore;
09804       if ( lastValueEnd_  &&  !containsNewLine( lastValueEnd_, commentBegin ) )
09805       {
09806          if ( c != '*'  ||  !containsNewLine( commentBegin, current_ ) )
09807             placement = commentAfterOnSameLine;
09808       }
09809 
09810       addComment( commentBegin, current_, placement );
09811    }
09812    return true;
09813 }
09814 
09815 
09816 void 
09817 Reader::addComment( Location begin, 
09818                     Location end, 
09819                     CommentPlacement placement ) {
09820    assert( collectComments_ );
09821    if ( placement == commentAfterOnSameLine )
09822    {
09823       assert( lastValue_ != 0 );
09824       lastValue_->setComment( std::string( begin, end ), placement );
09825    } else {
09826       if ( !commentsBefore_.empty() )
09827          commentsBefore_ += "\n";
09828       commentsBefore_ += std::string( begin, end );
09829    }
09830 }
09831 
09832 
09833 bool 
09834 Reader::readCStyleComment() {
09835    while ( current_ != end_ ) {
09836       Char c = getNextChar();
09837       if ( c == '*'  &&  *current_ == '/' )
09838          break;
09839    }
09840    return getNextChar() == '/';
09841 }
09842 
09843 
09844 bool 
09845 Reader::readCppStyleComment() {
09846    while ( current_ != end_ ) {
09847       Char c = getNextChar();
09848       if (  c == '\r'  ||  c == '\n' )
09849          break;
09850    }
09851    return true;
09852 }
09853 
09854 
09855 void 
09856 Reader::readNumber() {
09857    while ( current_ != end_ ) {
09858       if ( !(*current_ >= '0'  &&  *current_ <= '9')  &&
09859            !in( *current_, '.', 'e', 'E', '+', '-' ) )
09860          break;
09861       ++current_;
09862    }
09863 }
09864 
09865 bool
09866 Reader::readString() {
09867    Char c = 0;
09868    while ( current_ != end_ ) {
09869       c = getNextChar();
09870       if ( c == '\\' )
09871          getNextChar();
09872       else if ( c == '"' )
09873          break;
09874    }
09875    return c == '"';
09876 }
09877 
09878 
09879 bool 
09880 Reader::readObject( Token &/*tokenStart*/ ) {
09881    Token tokenName;
09882    std::string name;
09883    currentValue() = Value( objectValue );
09884    while ( readToken( tokenName ) ) {
09885       bool initialTokenOk = true;
09886       while ( tokenName.type_ == tokenComment  &&  initialTokenOk )
09887          initialTokenOk = readToken( tokenName );
09888       if  ( !initialTokenOk )
09889          break;
09890       if ( tokenName.type_ == tokenObjectEnd  &&  name.empty() )  // empty object
09891          return true;
09892       if ( tokenName.type_ != tokenString )
09893          break;
09894       
09895       name = "";
09896       if ( !decodeString( tokenName, name ) )
09897          return recoverFromError( tokenObjectEnd );
09898 
09899       Token colon;
09900       if ( !readToken( colon ) ||  colon.type_ != tokenMemberSeparator ) {
09901          return addErrorAndRecover( "Missing ':' after object member name", 
09902                                     colon, 
09903                                     tokenObjectEnd );
09904       }
09905       Value &value = currentValue()[ name ];
09906       nodes_.push( &value );
09907       bool ok = readValue();
09908       nodes_.pop();
09909       if ( !ok ) // error already set
09910          return recoverFromError( tokenObjectEnd );
09911 
09912       Token comma;
09913       if ( !readToken( comma )
09914             ||  ( comma.type_ != tokenObjectEnd  &&  
09915                   comma.type_ != tokenArraySeparator &&
09916                   comma.type_ != tokenComment ) ) {
09917          return addErrorAndRecover( "Missing ',' or '}' in object declaration", 
09918                                     comma, 
09919                                     tokenObjectEnd );
09920       }
09921       bool finalizeTokenOk = true;
09922       while ( comma.type_ == tokenComment &&
09923               finalizeTokenOk )
09924          finalizeTokenOk = readToken( comma );
09925       if ( comma.type_ == tokenObjectEnd )
09926          return true;
09927    }
09928    return addErrorAndRecover( "Missing '}' or object member name", 
09929                               tokenName, 
09930                               tokenObjectEnd );
09931 }
09932 
09933 
09934 bool 
09935 Reader::readArray( Token &/*tokenStart*/ ) {
09936    currentValue() = Value( arrayValue );
09937    skipSpaces();
09938    if ( *current_ == ']' ) { // empty array
09939       Token endArray;
09940       readToken( endArray );
09941       return true;
09942    }
09943    int index = 0;
09944    for (;;) {
09945       Value &value = currentValue()[ index++ ];
09946       nodes_.push( &value );
09947       bool ok = readValue();
09948       nodes_.pop();
09949       if ( !ok ) // error already set
09950          return recoverFromError( tokenArrayEnd );
09951 
09952       Token token;
09953       // Accept Comment after last item in the array.
09954       ok = readToken( token );
09955       while ( token.type_ == tokenComment  &&  ok ) {
09956          ok = readToken( token );
09957       }
09958       bool badTokenType = ( token.type_ != tokenArraySeparator  &&
09959                             token.type_ != tokenArrayEnd );
09960       if ( !ok  ||  badTokenType ) {
09961          return addErrorAndRecover( "Missing ',' or ']' in array declaration", 
09962                                     token, 
09963                                     tokenArrayEnd );
09964       }
09965       if ( token.type_ == tokenArrayEnd )
09966          break;
09967    }
09968    return true;
09969 }
09970 
09971 
09972 bool 
09973 Reader::decodeNumber( Token &token ) {
09974    bool isDouble = false;
09975    for ( Location inspect = token.start_; inspect != token.end_; ++inspect )
09976    {
09977       isDouble = isDouble  
09978                  ||  in( *inspect, '.', 'e', 'E', '+' )  
09979                  ||  ( *inspect == '-'  &&  inspect != token.start_ );
09980    }
09981    if ( isDouble )
09982       return decodeDouble( token );
09983    // Attempts to parse the number as an integer. If the number is
09984    // larger than the maximum supported value of an integer then
09985    // we decode the number as a double.
09986    Location current = token.start_;
09987    bool isNegative = *current == '-';
09988    if ( isNegative )
09989       ++current;
09990    Value::LargestUInt maxIntegerValue = isNegative ? Value::LargestUInt(-Value::minLargestInt) 
09991                                                    : Value::maxLargestUInt;
09992    Value::LargestUInt threshold = maxIntegerValue / 10;
09993    Value::UInt lastDigitThreshold = Value::UInt( maxIntegerValue % 10 );
09994    assert( lastDigitThreshold >=0  &&  lastDigitThreshold <= 9 );
09995    Value::LargestUInt value = 0;
09996    while ( current < token.end_ ) {
09997       Char c = *current++;
09998       if ( c < '0'  ||  c > '9' )
09999          return addError( "'" + std::string( token.start_, token.end_ ) + "' is not a number.", token );
10000       Value::UInt digit(c - '0');
10001       if ( value >= threshold ) {
10002          // If the current digit is not the last one, or if it is
10003          // greater than the last digit of the maximum integer value,
10004          // the parse the number as a double.
10005          if ( current != token.end_  ||  digit > lastDigitThreshold ) {
10006             return decodeDouble( token );
10007          }
10008       }
10009       value = value * 10 + digit;
10010    }
10011    if ( isNegative )
10012       currentValue() = -Value::LargestInt( value );
10013    else if ( value <= Value::LargestUInt(Value::maxInt) )
10014       currentValue() = Value::LargestInt( value );
10015    else
10016       currentValue() = value;
10017    return true;
10018 }
10019 
10020 
10021 bool 
10022 Reader::decodeDouble( Token &token ) {
10023    double value = 0;
10024    const int bufferSize = 32;
10025    int count;
10026    int length = int(token.end_ - token.start_);
10027    if ( length <= bufferSize ) {
10028       Char buffer[bufferSize+1];
10029       memcpy( buffer, token.start_, length );
10030       buffer[length] = 0;
10031       count = sscanf( buffer, "%lf", &value );
10032    } else {
10033       std::string buffer( token.start_, token.end_ );
10034       count = sscanf( buffer.c_str(), "%lf", &value );
10035    }
10036 
10037    if ( count != 1 )
10038       return addError( "'" + std::string( token.start_, token.end_ ) + "' is not a number.", token );
10039    currentValue() = value;
10040    return true;
10041 }
10042 
10043 
10044 bool 
10045 Reader::decodeString( Token &token ) {
10046    std::string decoded;
10047    if ( !decodeString( token, decoded ) )
10048       return false;
10049    currentValue() = decoded;
10050    return true;
10051 }
10052 
10053 
10054 bool 
10055 Reader::decodeString( Token &token, std::string &decoded ) {
10056    decoded.reserve( token.end_ - token.start_ - 2 );
10057    Location current = token.start_ + 1; // skip '"'
10058    Location end = token.end_ - 1;      // do not include '"'
10059    while ( current != end ) {
10060       Char c = *current++;
10061       if ( c == '"' )
10062          break;
10063       else if ( c == '\\' ) {
10064          if ( current == end )
10065             return addError( "Empty escape sequence in string", token, current );
10066          Char escape = *current++;
10067          switch ( escape ) {
10068          case '"': decoded += '"'; break;
10069          case '/': decoded += '/'; break;
10070          case '\\': decoded += '\\'; break;
10071          case 'b': decoded += '\b'; break;
10072          case 'f': decoded += '\f'; break;
10073          case 'n': decoded += '\n'; break;
10074          case 'r': decoded += '\r'; break;
10075          case 't': decoded += '\t'; break;
10076          case 'u': {
10077                unsigned int unicode;
10078                if ( !decodeUnicodeCodePoint( token, current, end, unicode ) )
10079                   return false;
10080                decoded += codePointToUTF8(unicode);
10081             }
10082             break;
10083          default:
10084             return addError( "Bad escape sequence in string", token, current );
10085          }
10086       }
10087       else {
10088          decoded += c;
10089       }
10090    }
10091    return true;
10092 }
10093 
10094 bool
10095 Reader::decodeUnicodeCodePoint( Token &token, 
10096                                      Location &current, 
10097                                      Location end, 
10098                                      unsigned int &unicode ) {
10099 
10100    if ( !decodeUnicodeEscapeSequence( token, current, end, unicode ) )
10101       return false;
10102    if (unicode >= 0xD800 && unicode <= 0xDBFF) {
10103       // surrogate pairs
10104       if (end - current < 6)
10105          return addError( "additional six characters expected to parse unicode surrogate pair.", token, current );
10106       unsigned int surrogatePair;
10107       if (*(current++) == '\\' && *(current++)== 'u') {
10108          if (decodeUnicodeEscapeSequence( token, current, end, surrogatePair )) {
10109             unicode = 0x10000 + ((unicode & 0x3FF) << 10) + (surrogatePair & 0x3FF);
10110          } else
10111             return false;
10112       } else
10113          return addError( "expecting another \\u token to begin the second half of a unicode surrogate pair", token, current );
10114    }
10115    return true;
10116 }
10117 
10118 bool 
10119 Reader::decodeUnicodeEscapeSequence( Token &token, 
10120                                      Location &current, 
10121                                      Location end, 
10122                                      unsigned int &unicode ) {
10123    if ( end - current < 4 )
10124       return addError( "Bad unicode escape sequence in string: four digits expected.", token, current );
10125    unicode = 0;
10126    for ( int index =0; index < 4; ++index ) {
10127       Char c = *current++;
10128       unicode *= 16;
10129       if ( c >= '0'  &&  c <= '9' )
10130          unicode += c - '0';
10131       else if ( c >= 'a'  &&  c <= 'f' )
10132          unicode += c - 'a' + 10;
10133       else if ( c >= 'A'  &&  c <= 'F' )
10134          unicode += c - 'A' + 10;
10135       else
10136          return addError( "Bad unicode escape sequence in string: hexadecimal digit expected.", token, current );
10137    }
10138    return true;
10139 }
10140 
10141 
10142 bool 
10143 Reader::addError( const std::string &message, 
10144                   Token &token,
10145                   Location extra ) {
10146    ErrorInfo info;
10147    info.token_ = token;
10148    info.message_ = message;
10149    info.extra_ = extra;
10150    errors_.push_back( info );
10151    return false;
10152 }
10153 
10154 
10155 bool 
10156 Reader::recoverFromError( TokenType skipUntilToken ) {
10157    int errorCount = int(errors_.size());
10158    Token skip;
10159    for (;;) {
10160       if ( !readToken(skip) )
10161          errors_.resize( errorCount ); // discard errors caused by recovery
10162       if ( skip.type_ == skipUntilToken  ||  skip.type_ == tokenEndOfStream )
10163          break;
10164    }
10165    errors_.resize( errorCount );
10166    return false;
10167 }
10168 
10169 
10170 bool 
10171 Reader::addErrorAndRecover( const std::string &message, 
10172                             Token &token,
10173                             TokenType skipUntilToken ) {
10174    addError( message, token );
10175    return recoverFromError( skipUntilToken );
10176 }

10180 Reader::currentValue() {
10181    return *(nodes_.top());
10182 }

10184 
10185 Reader::Char 
10186 Reader::getNextChar() {
10187    if ( current_ == end_ )
10188       return 0;
10189    return *current_++;
10190 }

10192 
10193 void 
10194 Reader::getLocationLineAndColumn( Location location,
10195                                   int &line,
10196                                   int &column ) const {
10197    Location current = begin_;
10198    Location lastLineStart = current;
10199    line = 0;
10200    while ( current < location  &&  current != end_ ) {
10201       Char c = *current++;
10202       if ( c == '\r' ) {
10203          if ( *current == '\n' )
10204             ++current;
10205          lastLineStart = current;
10206          ++line;
10207       } else if ( c == '\n' ) {
10208          lastLineStart = current;
10209          ++line;
10210       }
10211    }
10212    // column & line start at 1
10213    column = int(location - lastLineStart) + 1;
10214    ++line;
10215 }
10216 
10217 
10218 std::string
10219 Reader::getLocationLineAndColumn( Location location ) const {
10220    int line, column;
10221    getLocationLineAndColumn( location, line, column );
10222    char buffer[18+16+16+1];
10223    sprintf( buffer, "Line %d, Column %d", line, column );
10224    return buffer;
10225 }

10228 // Deprecated. Preserved for backward compatibility
10229 std::string 
10230 Reader::getFormatedErrorMessages() const {
10231     return getFormattedErrorMessages();
10232 }
10233 
10234 
10235 std::string 
10236 Reader::getFormattedErrorMessages() const {
10237    std::string formattedMessage;
10238    for ( Errors::const_iterator itError = errors_.begin();
10239          itError != errors_.end();
10240          ++itError ) {
10241       const ErrorInfo &error = *itError;
10242       formattedMessage += "* " + getLocationLineAndColumn( error.token_.start_ ) + "\n";
10243       formattedMessage += "  " + error.message_ + "\n";
10244       if ( error.extra_ )
10245          formattedMessage += "See " + getLocationLineAndColumn( error.extra_ ) + " for detail.\n";
10246    }
10247    return formattedMessage;
10248 }

10250 
10251 std::istream& operator>>( std::istream &sin, Value &root ) {
10252     Json::Reader reader;
10253     bool ok = reader.parse(sin, root, true);
10254     //JSON_ASSERT( ok );
10255     if (!ok) throw std::runtime_error(reader.getFormattedErrorMessages());
10256     return sin;
10257 }
